import { mutation, query } from "./_generated/server";
import { v } from "convex/values";

// Get goal members
export const getGoalMembers = query({
  args: { goalId: v.id("goals") },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    const members = await ctx.db
      .query("goal_members")
      .filter((q) => q.eq(q.field("goal_id"), args.goalId))
      .collect();

    // Get user details for each member
    const membersWithDetails = await Promise.all(
      members.map(async (member) => {
        const user = await ctx.db
          .query("users")
          .filter((q) => q.eq(q.field("id"), member.user_id))
          .first();
        
        return {
          ...member,
          user: user ? {
            id: user.id,
            email: user.email,
            name: user.name || user.email
          } : null
        };
      })
    );

    return membersWithDetails;
  },
});

// Get goal invitations
export const getGoalInvitations = query({
  args: { goalId: v.id("goals") },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    const invitations = await ctx.db
      .query("goal_invitations")
      .filter((q) => q.eq(q.field("goal_id"), args.goalId))
      .collect();

    // Get user details for each invitation
    const invitationsWithDetails = await Promise.all(
      invitations.map(async (invitation) => {
        const invitedUser = await ctx.db
          .query("users")
          .filter((q) => q.eq(q.field("id"), invitation.invited_user_id))
          .first();
        
        const invitedByUser = await ctx.db
          .query("users")
          .filter((q) => q.eq(q.field("id"), invitation.invited_by))
          .first();

        return {
          ...invitation,
          invitedUser: invitedUser ? {
            id: invitedUser.id,
            email: invitedUser.email,
            name: invitedUser.name || invitedUser.email
          } : null,
          invitedByUser: invitedByUser ? {
            id: invitedByUser.id,
            email: invitedByUser.email,
            name: invitedByUser.name || invitedByUser.email
          } : null
        };
      })
    );

    return invitationsWithDetails;
  },
});

// Get user's pending invitations
export const getUserPendingInvitations = query({
  args: { userId: v.string() },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    const invitations = await ctx.db
      .query("goal_invitations")
      .filter((q) => 
        q.and(
          q.eq(q.field("invited_user_id"), args.userId),
          q.eq(q.field("status"), "pending")
        )
      )
      .collect();

    // Get goal and inviter details
    const invitationsWithDetails = await Promise.all(
      invitations.map(async (invitation) => {
        const goal = await ctx.db
          .query("goals")
          .filter((q) => q.eq(q.field("id"), invitation.goal_id))
          .first();
        
        const inviter = await ctx.db
          .query("users")
          .filter((q) => q.eq(q.field("id"), invitation.invited_by))
          .first();

        return {
          ...invitation,
          goal: goal ? {
            id: goal.id,
            title: goal.title,
            category: goal.category,
            emoji: goal.emoji
          } : null,
          inviter: inviter ? {
            id: inviter.id,
            email: inviter.email,
            name: inviter.name || inviter.email
          } : null
        };
      })
    );

    return invitationsWithDetails;
  },
});

// Invite user to goal
export const inviteUserToGoal = mutation({
  args: {
    goalId: v.id("goals"),
    invitedUserId: v.string(),
    invitedBy: v.string(),
  },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    // Check if inviter is goal owner
    const member = await ctx.db
      .query("goal_members")
      .filter((q) => 
        q.and(
          q.eq(q.field("goal_id"), args.goalId),
          q.eq(q.field("user_id"), args.invitedBy),
          q.eq(q.field("role"), "owner")
        )
      )
      .first();

    if (!member) {
      throw new Error("Only goal owners can invite users");
    }

    // Check if user is already a member
    const existingMember = await ctx.db
      .query("goal_members")
      .filter((q) => 
        q.and(
          q.eq(q.field("goal_id"), args.goalId),
          q.eq(q.field("user_id"), args.invitedUserId)
        )
      )
      .first();

    if (existingMember) {
      throw new Error("User is already a member of this goal");
    }

    // Check if invitation already exists
    const existingInvitation = await ctx.db
      .query("goal_invitations")
      .filter((q) => 
        q.and(
          q.eq(q.field("goal_id"), args.goalId),
          q.eq(q.field("invited_user_id"), args.invitedUserId)
        )
      )
      .first();

    if (existingInvitation) {
      throw new Error("Invitation already sent to this user");
    }

    // Create invitation
    const invitationId = await ctx.db.insert("goal_invitations", {
      goal_id: args.goalId,
      invited_user_id: args.invitedUserId,
      invited_by: args.invitedBy,
      status: "pending",
      invited_at: new Date().toISOString(),
    });

    return invitationId;
  },
});

// Accept invitation
export const acceptInvitation = mutation({
  args: { invitationId: v.id("goal_invitations") },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    const invitation = await ctx.db.get(args.invitationId);
    if (!invitation) {
      throw new Error("Invitation not found");
    }

    // Update invitation status
    await ctx.db.patch(args.invitationId, {
      status: "accepted",
      responded_at: new Date().toISOString(),
    });

    // Add user as contributor
    await ctx.db.insert("goal_members", {
      goal_id: invitation.goal_id,
      user_id: invitation.invited_user_id,
      role: "contributor",
      joined_at: new Date().toISOString(),
    });

    return true;
  },
});

// Decline invitation
export const declineInvitation = mutation({
  args: { invitationId: v.id("goal_invitations") },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    const invitation = await ctx.db.get(args.invitationId);
    if (!invitation) {
      throw new Error("Invitation not found");
    }

    // Update invitation status
    await ctx.db.patch(args.invitationId, {
      status: "declined",
      responded_at: new Date().toISOString(),
    });

    return true;
  },
});

// Add contribution to goal
export const addContribution = mutation({
  args: {
    goalId: v.id("goals"),
    userId: v.string(),
    amount: v.number(),
    note: v.optional(v.string()),
  },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    // Check if user is a member
    const member = await ctx.db
      .query("goal_members")
      .filter((q) => 
        q.and(
          q.eq(q.field("goal_id"), args.goalId),
          q.eq(q.field("user_id"), args.userId),
          q.field("role").neq("viewer")
        )
      )
      .first();

    if (!member) {
      throw new Error("User cannot contribute to this goal");
    }

    // Add contribution
    const contributionId = await ctx.db.insert("goal_contributions", {
      goal_id: args.goalId,
      user_id: args.userId,
      amount: args.amount,
      note: args.note,
      contributed_at: new Date().toISOString(),
    });

    // Update goal progress
    const goal = await ctx.db.get(args.goalId);
    if (goal) {
      const newAmount = (goal.current_amount || 0) + args.amount;
      await ctx.db.patch(args.goalId, {
        current_amount: newAmount,
        completed: newAmount >= goal.target_amount,
      });
    }

    return contributionId;
  },
});

// Get goal contributions
export const getGoalContributions = query({
  args: { goalId: v.id("goals") },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    const contributions = await ctx.db
      .query("goal_contributions")
      .filter((q) => q.eq(q.field("goal_id"), args.goalId))
      .order("desc")
      .collect();

    // Get user details for each contribution
    const contributionsWithDetails = await Promise.all(
      contributions.map(async (contribution) => {
        const user = await ctx.db
          .query("users")
          .filter((q) => q.eq(q.field("id"), contribution.user_id))
          .first();
        
        return {
          ...contribution,
          user: user ? {
            id: user.id,
            email: user.email,
            name: user.name || user.email
          } : null
        };
      })
    );

    return contributionsWithDetails;
  },
});

// Remove member from goal (owner only)
export const removeMember = mutation({
  args: {
    goalId: v.id("goals"),
    userId: v.string(),
    removedBy: v.string(),
  },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    // Check if remover is goal owner
    const member = await ctx.db
      .query("goal_members")
      .filter((q) => 
        q.and(
          q.eq(q.field("goal_id"), args.goalId),
          q.eq(q.field("user_id"), args.removedBy),
          q.eq(q.field("role"), "owner")
        )
      )
      .first();

    if (!member) {
      throw new Error("Only goal owners can remove members");
    }

    // Cannot remove the owner
    if (args.userId === args.removedBy) {
      throw new Error("Cannot remove yourself as owner");
    }

    // Remove member
    const memberRecord = await ctx.db
      .query("goal_members")
      .filter((q) => 
        q.and(
          q.eq(q.field("goal_id"), args.goalId),
          q.eq(q.field("user_id"), args.userId)
        )
      )
      .first();

    if (memberRecord) {
      await ctx.db.delete(memberRecord._id);
    }

    return true;
  },
});










================================================
FILE: convex/schema.ts
================================================
import { defineSchema, defineTable } from "convex/server";
import { v } from "convex/values";

export default defineSchema({
  users: defineTable({
    name: v.string(),
    email: v.optional(v.string()),
    avatar: v.optional(v.string()),
    xp: v.number(),
    streak: v.number(),
    hearts: v.number(), // Current hearts (max 5)
    maxHearts: v.number(), // Maximum hearts (default 5)
    lastHeartLoss: v.optional(v.string()), // When hearts were last lost
    lastHeartReplenish: v.optional(v.string()), // When hearts were last replenished
    lastActiveDate: v.string(),
    financialLiteracyLevel: v.union(
      v.literal("beginner"),
      v.literal("intermediate"), 
      v.literal("advanced")
    ),
    onboardingCompleted: v.boolean(),
  }),

  lessons: defineTable({
    title: v.string(),
    description: v.string(),
    category: v.string(),
    difficulty: v.union(
      v.literal("beginner"),
      v.literal("intermediate"),
      v.literal("advanced")
    ),
    xpReward: v.number(),
    order: v.number(),
    content: v.array(v.object({
      type: v.union(
        v.literal("question"),
        v.literal("info"),
        v.literal("quiz")
      ),
      title: v.string(),
      content: v.string(),
      options: v.optional(v.array(v.string())),
      correctAnswer: v.optional(v.number()),
      explanation: v.optional(v.string()),
    })),
  }).index("by_category", ["category"])
    .index("by_difficulty", ["difficulty"])
    .index("by_order", ["order"]),

  userLessons: defineTable({
    userId: v.id("users"),
    lessonId: v.id("lessons"),
    completed: v.boolean(),
    score: v.optional(v.number()),
    completedAt: v.optional(v.string()),
  }).index("by_user", ["userId"])
    .index("by_user_and_lesson", ["userId", "lessonId"]),

  expenses: defineTable({
    userId: v.id("users"),
    amount: v.number(),
    category: v.string(),
    description: v.optional(v.string()),
    date: v.string(),
    createdAt: v.string(),
  }).index("by_user", ["userId"])
    .index("by_user_and_date", ["userId", "date"])
    .index("by_user_and_category", ["userId", "category"]),

  goals: defineTable({
    userId: v.id("users"),
    title: v.string(),
    description: v.optional(v.string()),
    targetAmount: v.number(),
    currentAmount: v.number(),
    deadline: v.string(),
    category: v.string(),
    completed: v.boolean(),
    createdAt: v.string(),
  }).index("by_user", ["userId"])
    .index("by_user_and_completed", ["userId", "completed"]),

  achievements: defineTable({
    userId: v.id("users"),
    type: v.union(
      v.literal("streak"),
      v.literal("lessons"),
      v.literal("expenses"),
      v.literal("goals"),
      v.literal("xp")
    ),
    title: v.string(),
    description: v.string(),
    icon: v.string(),
    unlockedAt: v.string(),
  }).index("by_user", ["userId"])
    .index("by_user_and_type", ["userId", "type"]),

  xpHistory: defineTable({
    userId: v.id("users"),
    xp: v.number(),
    source: v.string(),
    type: v.union(
      v.literal("lesson"),
      v.literal("quiz"),
      v.literal("challenge"),
      v.literal("achievement"),
      v.literal("streak"),
      v.literal("bonus")
    ),
    lessonId: v.optional(v.id("lessons")),
    quizId: v.optional(v.string()),
    date: v.string(),
    createdAt: v.string(),
  }).index("by_user", ["userId"])
    .index("by_user_and_date", ["userId", "date"])
    .index("by_user_and_type", ["userId", "type"]),

  leaderboard: defineTable({
    userId: v.id("users"),
    xp: v.number(),
    rank: v.number(),
    lastUpdated: v.string(),
  }).index("by_xp", ["xp"])
    .index("by_rank", ["rank"])
    .index("by_user", ["userId"]),

  heartHistory: defineTable({
    userId: v.id("users"),
    heartsChange: v.number(), // Positive for gain, negative for loss
    reason: v.string(), // "wrong_answer", "replenish", "bonus", etc.
    previousHearts: v.number(), // Hearts before change
    newHearts: v.number(), // Hearts after change
    timestamp: v.string(),
  }).index("by_user", ["userId"])
    .index("by_user_and_timestamp", ["userId", "timestamp"]),
});

FILE: convex/users.ts
================================================
import { query, mutation } from "./_generated/server";
import { v } from "convex/values";

export const create = mutation({
  args: {
    name: v.string(),
    email: v.optional(v.string()),
    avatar: v.optional(v.string()),
    financialLiteracyLevel: v.union(
      v.literal("beginner"),
      v.literal("intermediate"),
      v.literal("advanced")
    ),
  },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    const userId = await ctx.db.insert("users", {
      name: args.name,
      email: args.email,
      avatar: args.avatar,
      xp: 0,
      streak: 0,
      lastActiveDate: new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0],
      financialLiteracyLevel: args.financialLiteracyLevel,
      onboardingCompleted: false,
    });
    return userId;
  },
});

export const get = query({
  args: { userId: v.id("users") },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    return await ctx.db.get(args.userId);
  },
});

export const updateXP = mutation({
  args: {
    userId: v.id("users"),
    xpToAdd: v.number(),
  },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    const user = await ctx.db.get(args.userId);
    if (!user) throw new Error("User not found");

    const today = new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0];
    const yesterday = new Date(Date.now() - 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000).toISOString().split('T')[0];
    
    let newStreak = user.streak;
    if (user.lastActiveDate === yesterday) {
      newStreak += 1;
    } else if (user.lastActiveDate !== today) {
      newStreak = 1;
    }

    await ctx.db.patch(args.userId, {
      xp: user.xp + args.xpToAdd,
      streak: newStreak,
      lastActiveDate: today,
    });

    return { newXP: user.xp + args.xpToAdd, newStreak };
  },
});

export const completeOnboarding = mutation({
  args: { userId: v.id("users") },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    await ctx.db.patch(args.userId, {
      onboardingCompleted: true,
    });
  },
});

export const updateAvatar = mutation({
  args: {
    userId: v.id("users"),
    avatar: v.string(),
  },
  handler: async (ctx, args) => {
    await ctx.db.patch(args.userId, {
      avatar: args.avatar,
    });
  },
});

 * ```

  typeof fullApi,
  FunctionReference<any, "public">
>;

  typeof fullApi,
  FunctionReference<any, "internal">
>;

/* eslint-disable */
/**
 * Generated data model types.
 *
 * THIS CODE IS AUTOMATICALLY GENERATED.
 *
 * To regenerate, run `npx convex dev`.
 * @module
 */

import type {
  DataModelFromSchemaDefinition,
  DocumentByName,
  TableNamesInDataModel,
  SystemTableNames,
} from "convex/server";
import type { GenericId } from "convex/values";
import schema from "../schema.js";

/**
 * The names of all of your Convex tables.
 */
export type TableNames = TableNamesInDataModel<DataModel>;

/**
 * The type of a document stored in Convex.
 *
 * @typeParam TableName - A string literal type of the table name (like "users").
 */
export type Doc<TableName extends TableNames> = DocumentByName<
  DataModel,
  TableName
>;

/**
 * An identifier for a document in Convex.
 *
 * Convex documents are uniquely identified by their `Id`, which is accessible
 * on the `_id` field. To learn more, see [Document IDs](https://docs.convex.dev/using/document-ids).
 *
 * Documents can be loaded using `db.get(id)` in query and mutation functions.
 *
 * IDs are just strings at runtime, but this type can be used to distinguish them from other
 * strings when type checking.
 *
 * @typeParam TableName - A string literal type of the table name (like "users").
 */
export type Id<TableName extends TableNames | SystemTableNames> =
  GenericId<TableName>;

/**
 * A type describing your Convex data model.
 *
 * This type includes information about what tables you have, the type of
 * documents stored in those tables, and the indexes defined on them.
 *
 * This type is used to parameterize methods like `queryGeneric` and
 * `mutationGeneric` to make them type-safe.
 */
export type DataModel = DataModelFromSchemaDefinition<typeof schema>;

/**
 * Generated utilities for implementing server-side Convex query and mutation functions.
 *
 * THIS CODE IS AUTOMATICALLY GENERATED.
 *
 * To regenerate, run `npx convex dev`.
 * @module
 */

import {
  ActionBuilder,
  HttpActionBuilder,
  MutationBuilder,
  QueryBuilder,
  GenericActionCtx,
  GenericMutationCtx,
  GenericQueryCtx,
  GenericDatabaseReader,
  GenericDatabaseWriter,
} from "convex/server";
import type { DataModel } from "./dataModel.js";

/**
 * Define a query in this Convex app's public API.
 *
 * This function will be allowed to read your Convex database and will be accessible from the client.
 *
 * @param func - The query function. It receives a {@link QueryCtx} as its first argument.
 * @returns The wrapped query. Include this as an `export` to name it and make it accessible.
 */
export declare const query: QueryBuilder<DataModel, "public">;

/**
 * Define a query that is only accessible from other Convex functions (but not from the client).
 *
 * This function will be allowed to read from your Convex database. It will not be accessible from the client.
 *
 * @param func - The query function. It receives a {@link QueryCtx} as its first argument.
 * @returns The wrapped query. Include this as an `export` to name it and make it accessible.
 */
export declare const internalQuery: QueryBuilder<DataModel, "internal">;

/**
 * Define a mutation in this Convex app's public API.
 *
 * This function will be allowed to modify your Convex database and will be accessible from the client.
 *
 * @param func - The mutation function. It receives a {@link MutationCtx} as its first argument.
 * @returns The wrapped mutation. Include this as an `export` to name it and make it accessible.
 */
export declare const mutation: MutationBuilder<DataModel, "public">;

/**
 * Define a mutation that is only accessible from other Convex functions (but not from the client).
 *
 * This function will be allowed to modify your Convex database. It will not be accessible from the client.
 *
 * @param func - The mutation function. It receives a {@link MutationCtx} as its first argument.
 * @returns The wrapped mutation. Include this as an `export` to name it and make it accessible.
 */
export declare const internalMutation: MutationBuilder<DataModel, "internal">;

/**
 * Define an action in this Convex app's public API.
 *
 * An action is a function which can execute any JavaScript code, including non-deterministic
 * code and code with side-effects, like calling third-party services.
 * They can be run in Convex's JavaScript environment or in Node.js using the "use node" directive.
 * They can interact with the database indirectly by calling queries and mutations using the {@link ActionCtx}.
 *
 * @param func - The action. It receives an {@link ActionCtx} as its first argument.
 * @returns The wrapped action. Include this as an `export` to name it and make it accessible.
 */
export declare const action: ActionBuilder<DataModel, "public">;

/**
 * Define an action that is only accessible from other Convex functions (but not from the client).
 *
 * @param func - The function. It receives an {@link ActionCtx} as its first argument.
 * @returns The wrapped function. Include this as an `export` to name it and make it accessible.
 */
export declare const internalAction: ActionBuilder<DataModel, "internal">;

/**
 * Define an HTTP action.
 *
 * This function will be used to respond to HTTP requests received by a Convex
 * deployment if the requests matches the path and method where this action
 * is routed. Be sure to route your action in `convex/http.js`.
 *
 * @param func - The function. It receives an {@link ActionCtx} as its first argument.
 * @returns The wrapped function. Import this function from `convex/http.js` and route it to hook it up.
 */
export declare const httpAction: HttpActionBuilder;

/**
 * A set of services for use within Convex query functions.
 *
 * The query context is passed as the first argument to any Convex query
 * function run on the server.
 *
 * This differs from the {@link MutationCtx} because all of the services are
 * read-only.
 */
export type QueryCtx = GenericQueryCtx<DataModel>;

/**
 * A set of services for use within Convex mutation functions.
 *
 * The mutation context is passed as the first argument to any Convex mutation
 * function run on the server.
 */
export type MutationCtx = GenericMutationCtx<DataModel>;

/**
 * A set of services for use within Convex action functions.
 *
 * The action context is passed as the first argument to any Convex action
 * function run on the server.
 */
export type ActionCtx = GenericActionCtx<DataModel>;

/**
 * An interface to read from the database within Convex query functions.
 *
 * The two entry points are {@link DatabaseReader.get}, which fetches a single
 * document by its {@link Id}, or {@link DatabaseReader.query}, which starts
 * building a query.
 */
export type DatabaseReader = GenericDatabaseReader<DataModel>;

/**
 * An interface to read from and write to the database within Convex mutation
 * functions.
 *
 * Convex guarantees that all writes within a single mutation are
 * executed atomically, so you never have to worry about partial writes leaving
 * your data in an inconsistent state. See [the Convex Guide](https://docs.convex.dev/understanding/convex-fundamentals/functions#atomicity-and-optimistic-concurrency-control)
 * for the guarantees Convex provides your functions.
 */
export type DatabaseWriter = GenericDatabaseWriter<DataModel>;

 * Generated utilities for implementing server-side Convex query and mutation functions.

 * THIS CODE IS AUTOMATICALLY GENERATED.

 * To regenerate, run `npx convex dev`.
 * @module

import {
  actionGeneric,
  httpActionGeneric,
  queryGeneric,
  mutationGeneric,
  internalActionGeneric,
  internalMutationGeneric,
  internalQueryGeneric,
} from "convex/server";

/**
 * Define a query in this Convex app's public API.
 *
 * This function will be allowed to read your Convex database and will be accessible from the client.
 *
 * @param func - The query function. It receives a {@link QueryCtx} as its first argument.
 * @returns The wrapped query. Include this as an `export` to name it and make it accessible.
 */

 * Define a query that is only accessible from other Convex functions (but not from the client).
 *
 * This function will be allowed to read from your Convex database. It will not be accessible from the client.
 *
 * @param func - The query function. It receives a {@link QueryCtx} as its first argument.
 * @returns The wrapped query. Include this as an `export` to name it and make it accessible.
 */
export const internalQuery = internalQueryGeneric;

/**
 * Define a mutation in this Convex app's public API.

/**
 * Define a mutation that is only accessible from other Convex functions (but not from the client).
 *
 * This function will be allowed to modify your Convex database. It will not be accessible from the client.
 *
 * @param func - The mutation function. It receives a {@link MutationCtx} as its first argument.
 * @returns The wrapped mutation. Include this as an `export` to name it and make it accessible.
 */
export const internalMutation = internalMutationGeneric;

/**
 * Define an action in this Convex app's public API.
 *
 * An action is a function which can execute any JavaScript code, including non-deterministic
 * code and code with side-effects, like calling third-party services.
 * They can be run in Convex's JavaScript environment or in Node.js using the "use node" directive.
 * They can interact with the database indirectly by calling queries and mutations using the {@link ActionCtx}.
 *
 * @param func - The action. It receives an {@link ActionCtx} as its first argument.
 * @returns The wrapped action. Include this as an `export` to name it and make it accessible.
 */

 * Define an action that is only accessible from other Convex functions (but not from the client).

 */

 *
 * @param func - The function. It receives an {@link ActionCtx} as its first argument, and a `Request` object
 * as its second.
 * @returns The wrapped endpoint function. Route a URL path to this function in `convex/http.js`.
 */
export const httpAction = httpActionGeneric;



================================================
FILE: hooks/useHeartReplenishment.ts
================================================
import { useAuth } from '../contexts/AuthContext';
import { supabase } from '../services/supabase';

export const useHeartReplenishment = () => {
  const { user } = useAuth();

  // Manual heart status check (for immediate UI updates)
  const checkHeartStatus = async () => {
    if (!user) return;
    
    try {
      const heartPromise = supabase.functions.invoke('heart-management', {
        body: { action: 'get_heart_status', userId: user.id }
      });
      
      const timeoutPromise = new Promise((_, reject) => 
        setTimeout(() => reject(new Error('Heart status check timeout')), 10000)
      );
      
      const { data, error } = await Promise.race([heartPromise, timeoutPromise]) as any;

      if (error) throw error;
      return data;
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Error checking heart status:', error);
      return null;
    }
  };

  return {
    checkHeartStatus,
  };
};

FILE: scripts/check-table-structure.js
================================================
const { createClient } = require('@supabase/supabase-js');

const supabaseUrl = 'https://szikwcivaxpmurnzbbft.supabase.co';
const supabaseKey = 'eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZSIsInJlZiI6InN6aWt3Y2l2YXhwbXVybnpiYmZ0Iiwicm9sZSI6ImFub24iLCJpYXQiOjE3NTQ2Mjk1MTksImV4cCI6MjA3MDIwNTUxOX0.AF6MpJ0Rk6jIonStorAGo6S3kIt8H5bm5MzdrQmZQJ4';

const supabase = createClient(supabaseUrl, supabaseKey);

async function checkTableStructure() {
  try {
    console.log('ðŸ” Checking table structure...');
    
    // Try different possible table names
    const possibleTableNames = [
      'categories',
      'category',
      'chapters', 
      'chapter',
      'lessons',
      'lesson',
      'stories',
      'story',
      'story_pages',
      'storypages',
      'story_questions',
      'storyquestions',
      'story_answers',
      'storyanswers'
    ];

    for (const tableName of possibleTableNames) {
      try {
        console.log(`\nðŸ” Testing table: ${tableName}`);
        const { data, error } = await supabase
          .from(tableName)
          .select('*')
          .limit(1);
        
        if (error) {
          console.log(`âŒ Table ${tableName} not found or error:`, error.message);
        } else {
          console.log(`âœ… Table ${tableName} exists!`);
          if (data && data.length > 0) {
            console.log(`ðŸ“‹ Sample data structure:`, Object.keys(data[0]));
          }
        }
      } catch (err) {
        console.log(`âŒ Error testing ${tableName}:`, err.message);
      }
    }

    // Also try to get table list using RPC (if available)
    console.log('\nðŸ” Trying to get table list...');
    try {
      const { data: tables, error } = await supabase
        .rpc('get_table_names');
      
      if (error) {
        console.log('âŒ Could not get table list via RPC:', error.message);
      } else {
        console.log('âœ… Available tables:', tables);
      }
    } catch (err) {
      console.log('âŒ RPC not available or error:', err.message);
    }

  } catch (error) {
    console.error('âŒ Unexpected error:', error);
  }
}

// Run the check
checkTableStructure();

const { createClient } = require('@supabase/supabase-js');

// Supabase configuration
const supabaseUrl = 'https://szikwcivaxpmurnzbbft.supabase.co';
const supabaseKey = 'eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZSIsInJlZiI6InN6aWt3Y2l2YXhwbXVybnpiYmZ0Iiwicm9sZSI6ImFub24iLCJpYXQiOjE3NTQ2Mjk1MTksImV4cCI6MjA3MDIwNTUxOX0.AF6MpJ0Rk6jIonStorAGo6S3kIt8H5bm5MzdrQmZQJ4';

// Create Supabase client
const supabase = createClient(supabaseUrl, supabaseKey);

async function checkUsersTable() {
  console.log('ðŸ” Checking users table structure...\n');

  try {
    // Try to get a single user to see the table structure
    const { data, error } = await supabase
      .from('users')
      .select('*')
      .limit(1);

    if (error) {
      console.log('âŒ Error accessing users table:', error.message);
      return;
    }

    if (data && data.length > 0) {
      console.log('âœ… Users table exists!');
      console.log('ðŸ“‹ All columns:', Object.keys(data[0]));
      console.log('\nðŸ“‹ Sample user data:', data[0]);
      
      // Check for our new learning state columns
      const user = data[0];
      const learningColumns = [
        'selected_category_id',
        'current_chapter_id', 
        'current_course_index'
      ];
      
      console.log('\nðŸŽ¯ Checking for learning state columns:');
      learningColumns.forEach(col => {
        if (col in user) {
          console.log(`âœ… ${col}: ${user[col]}`);
        } else {
          console.log(`âŒ ${col}: NOT FOUND`);
        }
      });
      
    } else {
      console.log('âš ï¸ Users table exists but is empty');
    }

  } catch (error) {
    console.log('âŒ Unexpected error:', error.message);
  }
}

FILE: scripts/debug-connection.js
================================================
const { createClient } = require('@supabase/supabase-js');

const supabaseUrl = 'https://szikwcivaxpmurnzbbft.supabase.co';
const supabaseKey = 'eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZSIsInJlZiI6InN6aWt3Y2l2YXhwbXVybnpiYmZ0Iiwicm9sZSI6ImFub24iLCJpYXQiOjE3NTQ2Mjk1MTksImV4cCI6MjA3MDIwNTUxOX0.AF6MpJ0Rk6jIonStorAGo6S3kIt8H5bm5MzdrQmZQJ4';

const supabase = createClient(supabaseUrl, supabaseKey);

async function debugConnection() {
  try {
    console.log('ðŸ” Debugging database connection...');
    console.log('URL:', supabaseUrl);
    console.log('Key:', supabaseKey.substring(0, 20) + '...');
    
    // Test basic connection
    console.log('\nðŸ” Testing basic connection...');
    const { data: testData, error: testError } = await supabase
      .from('categories')
      .select('count(*)');
    
    if (testError) {
      console.error('âŒ Basic connection error:', testError);
      console.error('Error details:', JSON.stringify(testError, null, 2));
    } else {
      console.log('âœ… Basic connection successful');
      console.log('Count result:', testData);
    }

    // Test with different select patterns
    console.log('\nðŸ” Testing different select patterns...');
    
    // Test 1: Select all
    const { data: data1, error: error1 } = await supabase
      .from('categories')
      .select('*');
    console.log('Select * result:', data1?.length || 0, 'Error:', error1?.message || 'None');

    // Test 2: Select specific columns
    const { data: data2, error: error2 } = await supabase
      .from('categories')
      .select('id, name');
    console.log('Select specific columns result:', data2?.length || 0, 'Error:', error2?.message || 'None');

    // Test 3: Select with limit
    const { data: data3, error: error3 } = await supabase
      .from('categories')
      .select('*')
      .limit(5);
    console.log('Select with limit result:', data3?.length || 0, 'Error:', error3?.message || 'None');

    // Test 4: Check if table exists by trying to get schema
    console.log('\nðŸ” Testing table schema...');
    try {
      const { data: schemaData, error: schemaError } = await supabase
        .rpc('get_table_schema', { table_name: 'categories' });
      
      if (schemaError) {
        console.log('Schema RPC error:', schemaError.message);
      } else {
        console.log('Schema data:', schemaData);
      }
    } catch (err) {
      console.log('Schema RPC not available');
    }

    // Test 5: Try to insert a test record to see if it's a permissions issue
    console.log('\nðŸ” Testing insert permissions...');
    const { data: insertData, error: insertError } = await supabase
      .from('categories')
      .insert([
        {
          name: 'TEST CATEGORY',
          emoji: 'ðŸ§ª',
          description: 'This is a test category to check permissions'
        }
      ])
      .select();
    
    if (insertError) {
      console.log('Insert error:', insertError.message);
      console.log('This might indicate RLS policies are blocking access');
    } else {
      console.log('Insert successful:', insertData);
      
      // Clean up the test record
      if (insertData && insertData.length > 0) {
        const { error: deleteError } = await supabase
          .from('categories')
          .delete()
          .eq('name', 'TEST CATEGORY');
        
        if (deleteError) {
          console.log('Cleanup error:', deleteError.message);
        } else {
          console.log('Test record cleaned up');
        }
      }
    }

  } catch (error) {
    console.error('âŒ Unexpected error:', error);
  }
}

// Run the debug
debugConnection();

const { createClient } = require('@supabase/supabase-js');

// Supabase configuration
const supabaseUrl = 'https://szikwcivaxpmurnzbbft.supabase.co';
const supabaseKey = 'eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZSIsInJlZiI6InN6aWt3Y2l2YXhwbXVybnpiYmZ0Iiwicm9sZSI6ImFub24iLCJpYXQiOjE3NTQ2Mjk1MTksImV4cCI6MjA3MDIwNTUxOX0.AF6MpJ0Rk6jIonStorAGo6S3kIt8H5bm5MzdrQmZQJ4';

// Create Supabase client
const supabase = createClient(supabaseUrl, supabaseKey);

async function debugHearts() {
  console.log('ðŸ” Debugging hearts issue...\n');

  try {
    // Check if we can access the users table
    console.log('ðŸ“‹ Checking users table access...');
    const { data: users, error: usersError } = await supabase
      .from('users')
      .select('*')
      .limit(3);

    if (usersError) {
      console.log('âŒ Error accessing users table:', usersError.message);
      return;
    }

    if (users && users.length > 0) {
      console.log('âœ… Users table accessible');
      console.log('ðŸ“‹ All columns:', Object.keys(users[0]));
      
      console.log('\nðŸ“‹ Sample user data:');
      users.forEach((user, index) => {
        console.log(`\nUser ${index + 1}:`);
        console.log('  ID:', user.id);
        console.log('  Name:', user.name);
        console.log('  Email:', user.email);
        console.log('  Hearts:', user.hearts);
        console.log('  Max Hearts:', user.max_hearts);
        console.log('  Last Heart Loss:', user.last_heart_loss);
        console.log('  Last Heart Replenish:', user.last_heart_replenish);
        console.log('  XP:', user.xp);
        console.log('  Auth User ID:', user.auth_user_id);
      });
    } else {
      console.log('âš ï¸ Users table is empty');
    }

    // Check if heart columns exist
    console.log('\nðŸ’” Checking for heart-related columns...');
    const heartColumns = ['hearts', 'max_hearts', 'last_heart_loss', 'last_heart_replenish'];
    heartColumns.forEach(col => {
      if (users && users.length > 0 && col in users[0]) {
        console.log(`âœ… ${col}: exists`);
      } else {
        console.log(`âŒ ${col}: NOT FOUND`);
      }
    });

    // Check heart_history table
    console.log('\nðŸ“Š Checking heart_history table...');
    try {
      const { data: heartHistory, error: heartError } = await supabase
        .from('heart_history')
        .select('*')
        .limit(3);

      if (heartError) {
        console.log('âŒ Error accessing heart_history table:', heartError.message);
      } else if (heartHistory && heartHistory.length > 0) {
        console.log('âœ… heart_history table accessible');
        console.log('ðŸ“‹ Heart history columns:', Object.keys(heartHistory[0]));
        console.log('ðŸ“‹ Sample heart history:', heartHistory[0]);
      } else {
        console.log('âš ï¸ heart_history table exists but is empty');
      }
    } catch (error) {
      console.log('âŒ heart_history table error:', error.message);
    }

  } catch (error) {
    console.log('âŒ Unexpected error:', error.message);
  }
}

debugHearts();

  { name: 'Rabbit', emoji: 'ðŸ°' },
  { name: 'Bear', emoji: 'ðŸ»' },
  { name: 'Fox', emoji: 'ðŸ¦Š' },
];

function downloadEmoji(emojiName, emojiChar) {
  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
    const url = `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/microsoft/fluentui-emoji/main/assets/${emojiName}/3D/${emojiName.toLowerCase().replace(/%20/g, '_')}_3d.png`;
    const fileName = `${emojiName.toLowerCase().replace(/%20/g, '-')}.png`;
    const filePath = path.join(__dirname, '../assets/emojis', fileName);
    
    console.log(`Downloading ${emojiChar} (${emojiName})...`);
    
    https.get(url, (response) => {
      if (response.statusCode === 200) {
        const fileStream = fs.createWriteStream(filePath);
        response.pipe(fileStream);
        
        fileStream.on('finish', () => {
          fileStream.close();
          console.log(`âœ… Downloaded: ${fileName}`);
          resolve(fileName);
        });
        
        fileStream.on('error', (err) => {
          fs.unlink(filePath, () => {}); // Delete the file if there was an error
          reject(err);
        });
      } else {
        console.log(`âŒ Failed to download ${emojiName}: ${response.statusCode}`);
        resolve(null);
      }
    }).on('error', (err) => {
      console.log(`âŒ Error downloading ${emojiName}: ${err.message}`);
      resolve(null);
    });
  });
}

async function downloadAllEmojis() {
  console.log('ðŸš€ Starting Microsoft Fluent Emoji download...\n');
  
  // Ensure the emojis directory exists
  const emojisDir = path.join(__dirname, '../assets/emojis');
  if (!fs.existsSync(emojisDir)) {
    fs.mkdirSync(emojisDir, { recursive: true });
  }
  
  const results = [];
  
  for (const emoji of emojisToDownload) {
    try {
      const result = await downloadEmoji(emoji.name, emoji.emoji);
      if (result) {
        results.push({ ...emoji, fileName: result });
      }
      // Add a small delay to be respectful to the server
      await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 100));
    } catch (error) {
      console.log(`âŒ Error with ${emoji.name}: ${error.message}`);
    }
  }
  
  console.log('\nðŸ“Š Download Summary:');
  console.log(`âœ… Successfully downloaded: ${results.length} emojis`);
  console.log(`âŒ Failed: ${emojisToDownload.length - results.length} emojis`);
  
  if (results.length > 0) {
    console.log('\nðŸ“ Update your FluentEmoji.tsx component with these mappings:');
    console.log('// Add these to fluentEmojiMap:');
    results.forEach(({ emoji, fileName }) => {
      console.log(`  '${emoji}': require('../assets/emojis/${fileName}'),`);
    });
  }
}

// Run the download
downloadAllEmojis().catch(console.error);

const { createClient } = require('@supabase/supabase-js');

const supabaseUrl = 'https://szikwcivaxpmurnzbbft.supabase.co';

async function testDatabaseConnection() {
  try {
    console.log('ðŸ” Testing database connection...');
    
    // Test categories table
    console.log('\nðŸ“š Checking categories table...');
    const { data: categories, error: categoriesError } = await supabase
      .from('categories')
      .select('*');
    
    if (categoriesError) {
      console.error('âŒ Error fetching categories:', categoriesError);
    } else {
      console.log('âœ… Categories found:', categories?.length || 0);
      if (categories && categories.length > 0) {
        console.log('ðŸ“‹ Categories:', categories.map(c => `${c.emoji} ${c.name}`));
      }
    }

    // Test chapters table
    console.log('\nðŸ“– Checking chapters table...');
    const { data: chapters, error: chaptersError } = await supabase
      .from('chapters')
      .select('*');
    
    if (chaptersError) {
      console.error('âŒ Error fetching chapters:', chaptersError);
    } else {
      console.log('âœ… Chapters found:', chapters?.length || 0);
      if (chapters && chapters.length > 0) {
        console.log('ðŸ“‹ Chapters:', chapters.map(c => c.name));
      }
    }

    // Test lessons table
    console.log('\nðŸ“ Checking lessons table...');
    const { data: lessons, error: lessonsError } = await supabase
      .from('lessons')
      .select('*');
    
    if (lessonsError) {
      console.error('âŒ Error fetching lessons:', lessonsError);
    } else {
      console.log('âœ… Lessons found:', lessons?.length || 0);
      if (lessons && lessons.length > 0) {
        console.log('ðŸ“‹ Lessons:', lessons.map(l => l.name));
      }
    }

    // Test stories table
    console.log('\nðŸ“– Checking stories table...');
    const { data: stories, error: storiesError } = await supabase
      .from('stories')
      .select('*');
    
    if (storiesError) {
      console.error('âŒ Error fetching stories:', storiesError);
    } else {
      console.log('âœ… Stories found:', stories?.length || 0);
      if (stories && stories.length > 0) {
        console.log('ðŸ“‹ Stories:', stories.map(s => s.title));
      }
    }

    // Test story_pages table
    console.log('\nðŸ“„ Checking story_pages table...');
    const { data: pages, error: pagesError } = await supabase
      .from('story_pages')
      .select('*');
    
    if (pagesError) {
      console.error('âŒ Error fetching story pages:', pagesError);
    } else {
      console.log('âœ… Story pages found:', pages?.length || 0);
    }

    // Test story_questions table
    console.log('\nâ“ Checking story_questions table...');
    const { data: questions, error: questionsError } = await supabase
      .from('story_questions')
      .select('*');
    
    if (questionsError) {
      console.error('âŒ Error fetching questions:', questionsError);
    } else {
      console.log('âœ… Questions found:', questions?.length || 0);

    // Test story_answers table
    console.log('\nâœ… Checking story_answers table...');
    const { data: answers, error: answersError } = await supabase
      .from('story_answers')
      .select('*');
    
    if (answersError) {
      console.error('âŒ Error fetching answers:', answersError);
    } else {
      console.log('âœ… Answers found:', answers?.length || 0);
    }

    console.log('\nðŸŽ¯ Database connection test completed!');

  } catch (error) {
    console.error('âŒ Unexpected error:', error);
  }
}

FILE: scripts/update-users-hearts.js
================================================
const { createClient } = require('@supabase/supabase-js');
require('dotenv').config();

const supabaseUrl = process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL;
const supabaseKey = process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY;

if (!supabaseUrl || !supabaseKey) {
  console.error('âŒ Missing Supabase environment variables');
  process.exit(1);
}

const supabase = createClient(supabaseUrl, supabaseKey);

async function updateUsersWithHearts() {
  try {
    console.log('ðŸ”„ Starting heart system update...');

    // First, check if hearts column exists
    const { data: columns, error: columnError } = await supabase
      .from('users')
      .select('*')
      .limit(1);

    if (columnError) {
      console.error('âŒ Error checking users table:', columnError);
      return;
    }

    console.log('ðŸ“Š Current user columns:', Object.keys(columns[0]));

    // Check if hearts column exists
    const hasHearts = 'hearts' in columns[0];
    
    if (!hasHearts) {
      console.log('âš ï¸ Hearts column does not exist. You need to run the database migration first.');
      console.log('ðŸ“ Run this SQL command in your Supabase SQL editor:');
      console.log(`
        ALTER TABLE users 
        ADD COLUMN hearts INTEGER DEFAULT 5,
        ADD COLUMN max_hearts INTEGER DEFAULT 5,
        ADD COLUMN last_heart_loss TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE,
        ADD COLUMN last_heart_replenish TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE;
      `);
      return;
    }

    // Update all users to have default heart values
    const { data: users, error: usersError } = await supabase
      .from('users')
      .select('id, hearts, max_hearts')
      .or('hearts.is.null,max_hearts.is.null');

    if (usersError) {
      console.error('âŒ Error fetching users:', usersError);
      return;
    }

    if (users.length === 0) {
      console.log('âœ… All users already have heart data');
      return;
    }

    console.log(`ðŸ”„ Updating ${users.length} users with heart data...`);

    const now = new Date().toISOString();
    const updates = users.map(user => ({
      id: user.id,
      hearts: 5,
      max_hearts: 5,
      last_heart_replenish: now,
    }));

    const { error: updateError } = await supabase
      .from('users')
      .upsert(updates, { onConflict: 'id' });

    if (updateError) {
      console.error('âŒ Error updating users:', updateError);
      return;
    }

    console.log('âœ… Successfully updated all users with heart data');

    // Create heart_history table if it doesn't exist
    console.log('ðŸ”„ Creating heart_history table...');
    
    const { error: createTableError } = await supabase.rpc('exec_sql', {
      sql: `
        CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS heart_history (
          id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
          user_id UUID REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
          hearts_change INTEGER NOT NULL,
          reason TEXT NOT NULL,
          previous_hearts INTEGER NOT NULL,
          new_hearts INTEGER NOT NULL,
          timestamp TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT NOW()
        );
        
        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_heart_history_user_id ON heart_history(user_id);
        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_heart_history_timestamp ON heart_history(timestamp);
      `
    });

    if (createTableError) {
      console.log('âš ï¸ Could not create heart_history table via RPC. You may need to create it manually.');
      console.log('ðŸ“ Run this SQL command in your Supabase SQL editor:');
      console.log(`
        CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS heart_history (
          id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
          user_id UUID REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
          hearts_change INTEGER NOT NULL,
          reason TEXT NOT NULL,
          previous_hearts INTEGER NOT NULL,
          new_hearts INTEGER NOT NULL,
          timestamp TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT NOW()
        );
        
        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_heart_history_user_id ON heart_history(user_id);
        CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_heart_history_timestamp ON heart_history(timestamp);
      `);
    } else {
      console.log('âœ… Successfully created heart_history table');
    }

    console.log('ðŸŽ‰ Heart system setup complete!');
    console.log('ðŸ’¡ Users now have 5 hearts and will lose 1 heart per wrong answer');
    console.log('ðŸ’¡ Hearts will replenish automatically after 12 hours');

  } catch (error) {
    console.error('âŒ Unexpected error:', error);
  }
}

// Run the update
updateUsersWithHearts();

FILE: services/aiAnswerChecker.ts

// Simple Perplexity Sonar API client for intelligent answer evaluation
// Using direct fetch calls to avoid complex SDK issues

export interface AnswerEvaluation {
  isCorrect: boolean;
  confidence: number;
  feedback: string;
  score: number; // 0-100
}

export class AIAnswerChecker {
  
  // Method: Perplexity Sonar LLM Evaluation
  static async checkAnswerQuality(
    userAnswer: string,
    question: string,
    expectedKeywords?: string[]
  ): Promise<AnswerEvaluation> {
    try {
      console.log('ðŸ” Using Perplexity Sonar for answer evaluation...');
      console.log('ðŸ“ User Answer:', userAnswer);
      console.log('â“ Question:', question);
      
      // Create a clear prompt for the LLM
      const prompt = `You are evaluating answers for a financial literacy quiz. Provide a clear evaluation with reasoning.

Question: "${question}"

User's Answer: "${userAnswer}"

Evaluate this answer and respond in this exact format:

EVALUATION: [CORRECT or INCORRECT]
REASONING: [Brief explanation of why the answer is correct or incorrect]

Examples of INCORRECT answers:
- "I don't know", "no idea", "idk"
- Random characters like "Jk5etkcm"
- Generic responses like "yes", "no", "maybe"
- Unrelated content

Examples of CORRECT answers:
- Specific strategies with examples
- Clear explanations of concepts
- Practical advice related to the question

Provide constructive feedback that helps the user understand their answer quality.`;

      // Debug: Log the request details
      const requestBody = {
        model: 'sonar',
        messages: [
          {
            role: 'user',
            content: prompt
          }
        ]
      };
      
      console.log('ðŸ” DEBUG: Perplexity API Request Details:');
      console.log('ðŸ“¤ URL:', 'https://api.perplexity.ai/chat/completions');
      console.log('ðŸ”‘ API Key:', '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');
      console.log('ðŸ“¤ Request Body:', JSON.stringify(requestBody, null, 2));
      
      // Use direct fetch to Perplexity API (simplified format)
      const response = await fetch('https://api.perplexity.ai/chat/completions', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: {
          'Authorization': `Bearer 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`,
          'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        },
        body: JSON.stringify(requestBody)
      });

      console.log('ðŸ“¥ DEBUG: Response Status:', response.status);
      console.log('ðŸ“¥ DEBUG: Response Headers:', Object.fromEntries(response.headers.entries()));

      if (!response.ok) {
        const errorText = await response.text();
        console.error('âŒ DEBUG: Full Error Response:', errorText);
        throw new Error(`Perplexity API error: ${response.status}, body: ${errorText}`);
      }

      const result = await response.json();
      console.log('ðŸ“¥ Full API Response:', JSON.stringify(result, null, 2));
      
      // Parse Perplexity's response format (OpenAI-style)
      const aiResponse = result.choices?.[0]?.message?.content || '';
      console.log('ðŸ¤– Perplexity Sonar Response:', aiResponse);
      
      // Parse the structured response
      const cleanResponse = aiResponse.trim();
      const evaluationMatch = cleanResponse.match(/EVALUATION:\s*(CORRECT|INCORRECT)/i);
      const reasoningMatch = cleanResponse.match(/REASONING:\s*(.+)/i);
      
      const isCorrect = evaluationMatch ? evaluationMatch[1].toUpperCase() === 'CORRECT' : false;
      const aiReasoning = reasoningMatch ? reasoningMatch[1].trim() : '';
      const confidence = isCorrect ? 0.9 : 0.1; // High confidence for clear LLM responses
      
      // Use AI's reasoning as feedback, with fallback
      let feedback = '';
      if (aiReasoning) {
        feedback = aiReasoning;
      } else {
        // Fallback feedback if AI doesn't provide reasoning
        if (isCorrect) {
          feedback = 'Excellent answer! You clearly understand the concept and provided a thoughtful, detailed response.';
        } else {
          feedback = 'Your answer needs improvement. Please provide a more specific and detailed response that directly addresses the question with examples.';
        }
      }
      
      // Debug logging
      console.log('ðŸ” Perplexity Sonar Evaluation Debug:');
      console.log('ðŸ“ User Answer:', userAnswer);
      console.log('â“ Question:', question);
      console.log('ðŸ¤– AI Response:', aiResponse);
      console.log('âœ… Is Correct:', isCorrect);
      console.log('ðŸ“Š Confidence:', confidence);
      console.log('ðŸ“‹ Feedback:', feedback);
      
      return {
        isCorrect,
        confidence,
        feedback,
        score: Math.round(confidence * 100)
      };
      
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Perplexity Sonar evaluation error:', error);
      // Fallback to basic checking
      return this.fallbackCheck(userAnswer, question);
    }
  }
  
  // Fallback method when AI fails
  private static fallbackCheck(userAnswer: string, question: string): AnswerEvaluation {
    console.log('âš ï¸  Using fallback evaluation method');
    
    const userLower = userAnswer.toLowerCase().trim();
    
    // Check for meaningless responses
    const meaninglessResponses = [
      'i don\'t know', 'i have no idea', 'no idea', 'idk', 'dunno',
      'not sure', 'unsure', 'maybe', 'perhaps', 'i think', 'probably',
      'possibly', 'i guess', 'i suppose', 'no clue', 'beats me',
      'search me', 'pass', 'skip', 'next', 'i give up', 'i quit',
      'whatever', 'idc', 'i don\'t care'
    ];
    
    const isMeaningless = meaninglessResponses.some(meaningless => 
      userLower.includes(meaningless)
    );
    
    const isCorrect = !isMeaningless && userLower.length > 20;
    const confidence = isCorrect ? 0.7 : 0.2;
    
    let feedback = '';
    if (isCorrect) {
      feedback = 'Answer accepted! Your response shows effort and understanding.';
    } else {
      feedback = 'Please provide a more detailed and specific answer that addresses the question.';
    }
    
    return {
      isCorrect,
      confidence,
      feedback,
      score: Math.round(confidence * 100)
    };
  }
}
