    // Shopping
    { name: 'Amazon', category: 'Shopping', keywords: ['amazon'] },
    { name: 'Flipkart', category: 'Shopping', keywords: ['flipkart'] },
    { name: 'Myntra', category: 'Shopping', keywords: ['myntra'] },
    { name: 'Nykaa', category: 'Shopping', keywords: ['nykaa'] },
    { name: 'Reliance Digital', category: 'Shopping', keywords: ['reliance digital'] },
    { name: 'Croma', category: 'Shopping', keywords: ['croma'] },

    // Healthcare
    { name: 'Apollo Hospitals', category: 'Healthcare', keywords: ['apollo'] },
    { name: 'Fortis Healthcare', category: 'Healthcare', keywords: ['fortis'] },
    { name: 'Max Healthcare', category: 'Healthcare', keywords: ['max healthcare'] },
    { name: 'MedPlus', category: 'Healthcare', keywords: ['medplus'] },

    // Entertainment
    { name: 'Netflix', category: 'Entertainment', keywords: ['netflix'] },
    { name: 'Amazon Prime', category: 'Entertainment', keywords: ['amazon prime', 'prime video'] },
    { name: 'Disney+ Hotstar', category: 'Entertainment', keywords: ['hotstar', 'disney'] },
    { name: 'Spotify', category: 'Entertainment', keywords: ['spotify'] },
    { name: 'YouTube Premium', category: 'Entertainment', keywords: ['youtube premium'] },

    // Utilities
    { name: 'BSES', category: 'Utilities', keywords: ['bses'] },
    { name: 'Tata Power', category: 'Utilities', keywords: ['tata power'] },
    { name: 'Airtel', category: 'Utilities', keywords: ['airtel'] },
    { name: 'Jio', category: 'Utilities', keywords: ['jio'] },
    { name: 'Vodafone', category: 'Utilities', keywords: ['vodafone'] },
    { name: 'Idea', category: 'Utilities', keywords: ['idea'] },

    // Banks
    { name: 'HDFC Bank', category: 'Banking', keywords: ['hdfc'] },
    { name: 'SBI', category: 'Banking', keywords: ['sbi', 'state bank'] },
    { name: 'ICICI Bank', category: 'Banking', keywords: ['icici'] },
    { name: 'Axis Bank', category: 'Banking', keywords: ['axis'] },
    { name: 'Kotak Bank', category: 'Banking', keywords: ['kotak'] },
    { name: 'Yes Bank', category: 'Banking', keywords: ['yes bank'] },
    { name: 'PNB', category: 'Banking', keywords: ['pnb', 'punjab national bank'] }
  ];

  // Worldwide currency patterns
  private currencyPatterns = [
    // Indian Rupees
    /(?:rs\.?|â‚¹|inr)\s*(\d+(?:,\d+)*(?:\.\d{2})?)/i,
    /(\d+(?:,\d+)*(?:\.\d{2})?)\s*(?:rs\.?|â‚¹|inr)/i,
    
    // US Dollars
    /(?:usd|\$)\s*(\d+(?:,\d+)*(?:\.\d{2})?)/i,
    /(\d+(?:,\d+)*(?:\.\d{2})?)\s*(?:usd|\$)/i,
    
    // Euros
    /(?:eur|â‚¬)\s*(\d+(?:,\d+)*(?:\.\d{2})?)/i,
    /(\d+(?:,\d+)*(?:\.\d{2})?)\s*(?:eur|â‚¬)/i,
    
    // British Pounds
    /(?:gbp|Â£)\s*(\d+(?:,\d+)*(?:\.\d{2})?)/i,
    /(\d+(?:,\d+)*(?:\.\d{2})?)\s*(?:gbp|Â£)/i,
    
    // Japanese Yen
    /(?:jpy|Â¥)\s*(\d+(?:,\d+)*(?:\.\d{2})?)/i,
    /(\d+(?:,\d+)*(?:\.\d{2})?)\s*(?:jpy|Â¥)/i,
    
    // Australian Dollars
    /(?:aud|a\$)\s*(\d+(?:,\d+)*(?:\.\d{2})?)/i,
    /(\d+(?:,\d+)*(?:\.\d{2})?)\s*(?:aud|a\$)/i,
    
    // Canadian Dollars
    /(?:cad|c\$)\s*(\d+(?:,\d+)*(?:\.\d{2})?)/i,
    /(\d+(?:,\d+)*(?:\.\d{2})?)\s*(?:cad|c\$)/i,
    
    // Generic currency patterns (for other currencies)
    /(?:amount|amt|bal|balance)\s*:?\s*(\d+(?:,\d+)*(?:\.\d{2})?)/i,
    /(\d+(?:,\d+)*(?:\.\d{2})?)\s*(?:amount|amt|bal|balance)/i
  ];

  // Transaction-specific patterns with currency
  private transactionPatterns = [
    // Patterns with specific transaction keywords and currency
    /(?:sent|debited|withdrawal)\s*(?:rs\.?|â‚¹|inr|usd|\$|eur|â‚¬|gbp|Â£|jpy|Â¥|aud|a\$|cad|c\$)?\s*(\d+(?:,\d+)*(?:\.\d{2})?)/i,
    /(?:credited|received|deposited)\s*(?:rs\.?|â‚¹|inr|usd|\$|eur|â‚¬|gbp|Â£|jpy|Â¥|aud|a\$|cad|c\$)?\s*(\d+(?:,\d+)*(?:\.\d{2})?)/i,
    
    // Specific pattern for "Credited for Rs:amount" format
    /(?:credited|received|deposited)\s+for\s+(?:rs\.?|â‚¹|inr)\s*:?\s*(\d+(?:,\d+)*(?:\.\d{2})?)/i,
    
    // Specific pattern for "Debited for Rs:amount" format
    /(?:sent|debited|withdrawal)\s+for\s+(?:rs\.?|â‚¹|inr)\s*:?\s*(\d+(?:,\d+)*(?:\.\d{2})?)/i,
    
    // Card transaction patterns with currency - ONLY if core keywords are present
    /(?:card|credit|debit)\s*(?:transaction|payment)?\s*(?:of|for)?\s*(?:rs\.?|â‚¹|inr|usd|\$|eur|â‚¬|gbp|Â£|jpy|Â¥|aud|a\$|cad|c\$)?\s*(\d+(?:,\d+)*(?:\.\d{2})?)/i
  ];

  // Core transaction keywords - ONLY these should trigger processing
  private transactionKeywords = [
    'sent', 'debited', 'withdrawal', 'credited', 'received', 'deposited'
  ];

  // Keywords to ignore (promotional and non-transactional messages)
  private ignoreKeywords = [
    'get credit card', 'get debit card', 'credit card issued', 'debit card issued',
    'card delivered', 'card dispatched', 'card activated', 'card blocked',
    'enjoying fd', 'fd-backed', 'benefits worth', 't&c', 'terms and conditions',
    'promotional', 'offer', 'discount', 'cashback offer', 'reward points',
    'hello', 'customer', 'enjoy', 'get more', 'enjoy benefits',
    'missed call', 'missed calls', 'balance enquiry', 'balance check', 'account balance enquiry'
  ];

  async detectExpenses(messages: SmsMessage[]): Promise<TransactionData[]> {
    const transactions: TransactionData[] = [];

    for (const message of messages) {
      const transaction = this.parseTransaction(message);
      if (transaction) {
        transactions.push(transaction);
      }
    }

    return transactions.sort((a, b) => b.date.getTime() - a.date.getTime());
  }

  private parseTransaction(message: SmsMessage): TransactionData | null {
    const body = message.body.toLowerCase();
    
    console.log('ðŸ” Processing message:', body.substring(0, 100) + '...');
    
    // Check if message should be ignored
    if (this.shouldIgnoreMessage(body)) {
      console.log('âŒ Message ignored due to ignore keywords');
      return null;
    }

    // FIRST: Check if it's a financial message with EXACT transaction keywords
    if (!this.isFinancialMessage(body)) {
      console.log('âŒ Message ignored - no transaction keywords found');
      return null;
    }

    console.log('âœ… Message has transaction keywords, proceeding...');

    // SECOND: Only extract amount if transaction keywords are present
    const amountResult = this.extractAmountWithCurrency(body);
    if (amountResult.amount === 0) {
      console.log('âŒ No amount extracted');
      return null;
    }

    console.log('âœ… Amount extracted:', amountResult.amount);

    // THIRD: Determine transaction type using core keywords
    const type = this.determineTransactionType(body);
    if (!type) {
      console.log('âŒ No transaction type determined');
      return null;
    }

    console.log('âœ… Transaction type:', type);

    // FOURTH: Extract merchant and category
    const { merchant, category } = this.detectMerchantAndCategory(body);

    // FIFTH: Extract bank info
    const bank = this.extractBankInfo(body, message.address);

    console.log('âœ… Transaction created:', { amount: amountResult.amount, type, category, merchant });

    // Use the actual SMS message date, but validate it's not a future date
    let messageDate = new Date(message.date);
    console.log('ðŸ“… Original message date:', messageDate.toISOString(), 'for message:', body.substring(0, 50));
    
    // If the message date is in the future, use current date instead
    const now = new Date();
    if (messageDate > now) {
      console.log('âš ï¸ Message date is in the future, using current date instead');
      messageDate = now;
    }
    
    console.log('ðŸ“… Final message date:', messageDate.toISOString());
    
    // Generate unique ID if message.id is null
    const uniqueId = message.id || `sms_${message.date}_${Math.random().toString(36).substr(2, 9)}`;
    
    return {
      id: uniqueId,
      amount: amountResult.amount,
      description: this.extractDescription(body),
      category: category,
      date: messageDate,
      type: type,
      bank: bank,
      account: message.address
    };
  }

  private shouldIgnoreMessage(body: string): boolean {
    return this.ignoreKeywords.some(keyword => body.includes(keyword.toLowerCase()));
  }

  private isFinancialMessage(body: string): boolean {
    // Convert to lowercase first for case-insensitive matching
    const lowerBody = body.toLowerCase();
    
    // ONLY check for exact transaction keywords with word boundaries - this is the FIRST filter
    const foundKeywords = this.transactionKeywords.filter(keyword => {
      const regex = new RegExp(`\\b${keyword}\\b`, 'i');
      return regex.test(lowerBody);
    });
    
    // Special test for the problematic message
    if (lowerBody.includes('upi autopay mandate') || lowerBody.includes('google cloud') || lowerBody.includes('credited for rs') || lowerBody.includes('debited for rs')) {
      console.log('ðŸš¨ TESTING PROBLEMATIC MESSAGE:');
      console.log('ðŸ” Message body:', body);
      console.log('ðŸ” Lowercase body:', lowerBody);
      console.log('ðŸ” Transaction keywords:', this.transactionKeywords);
      console.log('ðŸ” Found keywords:', foundKeywords);
      
      // Check each keyword individually with word boundaries
      for (const keyword of this.transactionKeywords) {
        const regex = new RegExp(`\\b${keyword}\\b`, 'i');
        if (regex.test(lowerBody)) {
          console.log(`ðŸ” FOUND KEYWORD: "${keyword}" in message`);
        }
      }
    }
    
    const result = this.transactionKeywords.some(keyword => {
      const regex = new RegExp(`\\b${keyword}\\b`, 'i');
      return regex.test(lowerBody);
    });
    
    if (lowerBody.includes('upi autopay mandate') || lowerBody.includes('google cloud') || lowerBody.includes('credited for rs') || lowerBody.includes('debited for rs')) {
      console.log('ðŸ” isFinancialMessage result:', result);
    }
    
    return result;
  }

  private extractAmountWithCurrency(body: string): { amount: number; currency: string } {
    // This method is ONLY called if transaction keywords are already confirmed present
    // So we don't need to check again - just extract the amount

    // First try transaction-specific patterns (these already include transaction keywords)
    for (const pattern of this.transactionPatterns) {
      const match = body.match(pattern);
      if (match) {
        const amountStr = match[1].replace(/,/g, '');
        const amount = parseFloat(amountStr);
        if (!isNaN(amount) && amount > 0) {
          return { amount, currency: 'INR' }; // Default to INR for now
        }
      }
    }

    // Then try general currency patterns (since we know transaction keywords are present)
    for (const pattern of this.currencyPatterns) {
      const match = body.match(pattern);
      if (match) {
        const amountStr = match[1].replace(/,/g, '');
        const amount = parseFloat(amountStr);
        if (!isNaN(amount) && amount > 0) {
          return { amount, currency: 'INR' }; // Default to INR for now
        }
      }
    }

    return { amount: 0, currency: '' };
  }

  private determineTransactionType(body: string): 'credit' | 'debit' | null {
    // Convert to lowercase first for case-insensitive matching
    const lowerBody = body.toLowerCase();
    
    // Check for core credit keywords with word boundaries
    const isCredit = ['credited', 'received', 'deposited'].some(keyword => {
      const regex = new RegExp(`\\b${keyword}\\b`, 'i');
      return regex.test(lowerBody);
    });
    
    const isDebit = ['sent', 'debited', 'withdrawal'].some(keyword => {
      const regex = new RegExp(`\\b${keyword}\\b`, 'i');
      return regex.test(lowerBody);
    });

    // If only one type of keyword is present, use that
    if (isCredit && !isDebit) return 'credit';
    if (isDebit && !isCredit) return 'debit';
    
    // If both keywords are present, use more sophisticated logic
    if (isCredit && isDebit) {
      // Look for the FIRST occurrence of each keyword to determine primary action
      const creditKeywords = ['credited', 'received', 'deposited'];
      const debitKeywords = ['sent', 'debited', 'withdrawal'];
      
      let firstCreditIndex = -1;
      let firstDebitIndex = -1;
      
      // Find the first occurrence of each type
      for (const keyword of creditKeywords) {
        const index = lowerBody.indexOf(keyword);
        if (index !== -1 && (firstCreditIndex === -1 || index < firstCreditIndex)) {
          firstCreditIndex = index;
        }
      }
      
      for (const keyword of debitKeywords) {
        const index = lowerBody.indexOf(keyword);
        if (index !== -1 && (firstDebitIndex === -1 || index < firstDebitIndex)) {
          firstDebitIndex = index;
        }
      }
      
      // If one appears before the other, prioritize the first one
      if (firstCreditIndex !== -1 && firstDebitIndex !== -1) {
        if (firstDebitIndex < firstCreditIndex) {
          return 'debit';
        } else {
          return 'credit';
        }
      }
      
      // If we can't determine order, check for specific patterns
      // Look for "debited for rs" or "credited for rs" patterns
      if (lowerBody.includes('debited for rs') || lowerBody.includes('debited for â‚¹')) {
        return 'debit';
      }
      if (lowerBody.includes('credited for rs') || lowerBody.includes('credited for â‚¹')) {
        return 'credit';
      }
      
      // Default to debit if ambiguous (more common for outgoing transactions)
      return 'debit';
    }

    return null;
  }

  private detectMerchantAndCategory(body: string): { merchant: string; category: string } {
    // First try to match known merchants
    for (const merchant of this.merchants) {
      if (merchant.keywords.some(keyword => body.includes(keyword))) {
        return {
          merchant: merchant.name,
          category: merchant.category
        };
      }
    }

    // If no merchant match, try category keywords
    for (const category of this.categories) {
      if (category.keywords.some(keyword => body.includes(keyword))) {
        return {
          merchant: this.extractMerchantFromBody(body),
          category: category.name
        };
      }
    }

    // Default fallback
    return {
      merchant: this.extractMerchantFromBody(body),
      category: 'Other'
    };
  }

  private extractMerchantFromBody(body: string): string {
    // Try to extract merchant name from common patterns
    const patterns = [
      /(?:at|from|to|via|through)\s+([a-zA-Z\s&]+(?:store|shop|restaurant|cafe|hospital|bank))/i,
      /(?:merchant|vendor)\s*:?\s*([a-zA-Z\s&]+)/i,
      /(?:upi\s+to|payment\s+to)\s+([a-zA-Z\s&]+)/i
    ];

    for (const pattern of patterns) {
      const match = body.match(pattern);
      if (match) {
        return match[1].trim();
      }
    }

    return 'Unknown Merchant';
  }

  private extractBankInfo(body: string, sender: string): string {
    // Try to extract bank name from message body
    const bankPatterns = [
      /(?:from|via|through)\s+([a-zA-Z\s]+(?:bank|card))/i,
      /(?:account|card)\s+([a-zA-Z\s]+(?:bank))/i
    ];

    for (const pattern of bankPatterns) {
      const match = body.match(pattern);
      if (match) {
        return match[1].trim();
      }
    }

    // Check for specific bank names in the message body
    if (body.toLowerCase().includes('union bank of india')) return 'Union Bank of India';
    if (body.toLowerCase().includes('hdfc bank')) return 'HDFC Bank';
    if (body.toLowerCase().includes('sbi')) return 'SBI';
    if (body.toLowerCase().includes('icici bank')) return 'ICICI Bank';
    if (body.toLowerCase().includes('axis bank')) return 'Axis Bank';
    if (body.toLowerCase().includes('kotak bank')) return 'Kotak Bank';

    // If not found in body, try to infer from sender
    if (sender.toLowerCase().includes('hdfc')) return 'HDFC Bank';
    if (sender.toLowerCase().includes('sbi')) return 'SBI';
    if (sender.toLowerCase().includes('icici')) return 'ICICI Bank';
    if (sender.toLowerCase().includes('axis')) return 'Axis Bank';
    if (sender.toLowerCase().includes('kotak')) return 'Kotak Bank';
    if (sender.toLowerCase().includes('union')) return 'Union Bank of India';

    return 'Unknown Bank';
  }

  private extractDescription(body: string): string {
    // Try to extract meaningful description
    const lines = body.split('\n');
    
    for (const line of lines) {
      const trimmedLine = line.trim();
      if (trimmedLine && 
          (trimmedLine.includes('at') || 
           trimmedLine.includes('from') || 
           trimmedLine.includes('to') ||
           trimmedLine.includes('via'))) {
        return trimmedLine;
      }
    }

    // Fallback: return first meaningful line
    for (const line of lines) {
      const trimmedLine = line.trim();
      if (trimmedLine && trimmedLine.length > 10) {
        return trimmedLine.substring(0, 50) + (trimmedLine.length > 50 ? '...' : '');
      }
    }

    return body.substring(0, 50) + '...';
  }

  getCategories(): ExpenseCategory[] {
    return this.categories;
  }

  getMerchants(): MerchantInfo[] {
    return this.merchants;
  }

  // Check if a message is a transaction message
  async isTransactionMessage(message: SmsMessage): Promise<boolean> {
    const body = message.body.toLowerCase();
    
    console.log(`ðŸ” Checking message:`, body.substring(0, 100));
    
    // Check if message should be ignored
    if (this.shouldIgnoreMessage(body)) {
      console.log(`âŒ Message ignored due to ignore keywords`);
      return false;
    }

    // Check if it's a financial message with transaction keywords
    const isFinancial = this.isFinancialMessage(body);
    console.log(`ðŸ’° Is financial message:`, isFinancial);
    
    return isFinancial;
  }

  // Extract transaction data from a single message
  async extractTransactionFromMessage(message: SmsMessage): Promise<TransactionData | null> {
    return this.parseTransaction(message);
  }
}

export default new ExpenseDetector(); 


================================================
FILE: services/goalsService.ts
================================================
import { supabase } from './supabase';

export interface Goal {
  id: string;
  user_id: string;
  title: string;
  description?: string;
  target_amount: number;
  current_amount: number;
  deadline: string;
  category: string;
  emoji: string;
  color: string;
  completed: boolean;
  created_at: string;
  updated_at: string;
  isCreator?: boolean; // Whether the current user is the creator of this goal
  role?: string; // Role of the current user in this goal (creator, contributor)
}

export interface CreateGoalData {
  title: string;
  description?: string;
  target_amount: number;
  deadline: string;
  category: string;
  emoji: string;
  color?: string;
}

export interface UpdateGoalProgressData {
  amount: number;
}

export class GoalsService {
  // Get all goals for the current user from goal_members table
  static async getGoals(): Promise<Goal[]> {
    // Get the current authenticated user
    const { data: { user }, error: authError } = await supabase.auth.getUser();
    
    if (authError || !user) {
      throw new Error('User not authenticated');
    }

    // Get the user from the public.users table using auth_user_id
    const { data: publicUser, error: userError } = await supabase
      .from('users')
      .select('id')
      .eq('auth_user_id', user.id)
      .single();

    if (userError || !publicUser) {
      throw new Error('User profile not found');
    }

    // Get all goals the user is a member of from goal_members table
    const { data: goalMemberships, error: membershipsError } = await supabase
      .from('goal_members')
      .select(`
        role,
        joined_at,
        goals (
          id,
          user_id,
          title,
          description,
          target_amount,
          current_amount,
          deadline,
          category,
          emoji,
          color,
          completed,
          created_at,
          updated_at
        )
      `)
      .eq('user_id', publicUser.id)
      .order('joined_at', { ascending: false });

    if (membershipsError) {
      console.error('Error fetching goal memberships:', membershipsError);
      throw membershipsError;
    }

    // Transform the data to match the Goal interface
    const goalsWithRole = (goalMemberships || [])
      .map(membership => {
        const goal = membership.goals;
        if (!goal) return null;
        
        return {
          ...goal,
          isCreator: goal.user_id === user.id, // Check if user is the creator
          role: membership.role // 'owner', 'contributor', or 'viewer'
        };
      })
      .filter(Boolean) // Remove any null entries
      .sort((a, b) => new Date(b.created_at).getTime() - new Date(a.created_at).getTime());

    return goalsWithRole;
  }

  // Get a specific goal by ID (only if user is a member)
  static async getGoalById(goalId: string): Promise<Goal> {
    // Get the current authenticated user
    const { data: { user }, error: authError } = await supabase.auth.getUser();
    
    if (authError || !user) {
      throw new Error('User not authenticated');
    }

    // Get the user from the public.users table using auth_user_id
    const { data: publicUser, error: userError } = await supabase
      .from('users')
      .select('id')
      .eq('auth_user_id', user.id)
      .single();
    
    if (userError || !publicUser) {
      throw new Error('User profile not found');
    }

    // Check if user is a member of this goal
    const { data: membership, error: membershipError } = await supabase
      .from('goal_members')
      .select(`
        role,
        goals (
          id,
          user_id,
          title,
          description,
          target_amount,
          current_amount,
          deadline,
          category,
          emoji,
          color,
          completed,
          created_at,
          updated_at
        )
      `)
      .eq('goal_id', goalId)
      .eq('user_id', publicUser.id)
      .single();

    if (membershipError || !membership || !membership.goals) {
      throw new Error('Goal not found or access denied');
    }

    const goal = membership.goals;
    
    return {
      ...goal,
      isCreator: goal.user_id === user.id,
      role: membership.role
    };
  }

  // Create a new goal
  static async createGoal(goalData: CreateGoalData): Promise<Goal> {
    // Get the current authenticated user
    const { data: { user }, error: authError } = await supabase.auth.getUser();
    
    if (authError || !user) {
      throw new Error('User not authenticated');
    }

    // Get the user from the public.users table using auth_user_id
    const { data: publicUser, error: userError } = await supabase
      .from('users')
      .select('id')
      .eq('auth_user_id', user.id)
      .single();

    if (userError || !publicUser) {
      throw new Error('User profile not found');
    }

    // Start a transaction to create goal and add user as owner
    const { data: goal, error: goalError } = await supabase
      .from('goals')
      .insert([{
        ...goalData,
        user_id: user.id,
        color: goalData.color || '#A2E57B'
      }])
      .select()
      .single();

    if (goalError) {
      console.error('Error creating goal:', goalError);
      throw goalError;
    }

    // Add the user as owner in goal_members table using public.users.id
    const { error: memberError } = await supabase
      .from('goal_members')
      .insert([{
        goal_id: goal.id,
        user_id: publicUser.id,
        role: 'owner'
      }]);

    if (memberError) {
      console.error('Error adding user as goal owner:', memberError);
      // Note: We don't throw here as the goal was created successfully
      // The user can still access their goal, just won't be in the members table
    }

    return goal;
  }

  // Update goal progress
  static async updateProgress(goalId: string, amount: number): Promise<Goal> {
    // First get the current goal to calculate new amount
    const { data: currentGoal, error: fetchError } = await supabase
      .from('goals')
      .select('current_amount, target_amount')
      .eq('id', goalId)
      .single();

    if (fetchError) {
      console.error('Error fetching goal:', fetchError);
      throw fetchError;
    }

    const newAmount = Math.max(0, currentGoal.current_amount + amount);
    const isCompleted = newAmount >= currentGoal.target_amount;

    const { data, error } = await supabase
      .from('goals')
      .update({
        current_amount: newAmount,
        completed: isCompleted,
        updated_at: new Date().toISOString()
      })
      .eq('id', goalId)
      .select()
      .single();

    if (error) {
      console.error('Error updating goal:', error);
      throw error;
    }

    return data;
  }

  // Delete a goal
  static async deleteGoal(goalId: string): Promise<void> {
    const { error } = await supabase
      .from('goals')
      .delete()
      .eq('id', goalId);

    if (error) {
      console.error('Error deleting goal:', error);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  // Get goal statistics
  static async getGoalStats(): Promise<{
    totalGoals: number;
    completedGoals: number;
    activeGoals: number;
    totalProgress: number;
  }> {
    const { data, error } = await supabase
      .from('goals')
      .select('target_amount, current_amount, completed');

    if (error) {
      console.error('Error fetching goal stats:', error);
      throw error;
    }

    const totalGoals = data.length;
    const completedGoals = data.filter(g => g.completed).length;
    const activeGoals = totalGoals - completedGoals;
    
    const totalProgress = data.reduce((sum, goal) => {
      if (goal.completed) return sum + 100;
      return sum + (goal.current_amount / goal.target_amount) * 100;
    }, 0);

    return {
      totalGoals,
      completedGoals,
      activeGoals,
      totalProgress: totalGoals > 0 ? totalProgress / totalGoals : 0
    };
  }

  // Get goals by category
  static async getGoalsByCategory(category: string): Promise<Goal[]> {
    const { data, error } = await supabase
      .from('goals')
      .select('*')
      .eq('category', category)
      .order('created_at', { ascending: false });

    if (error) {
      console.error('Error fetching goals by category:', error);
      throw error;
    }

    return data || [];
  }

  // Get upcoming deadlines
  static async getUpcomingDeadlines(days: number = 30): Promise<Goal[]> {
    const futureDate = new Date();
    futureDate.setDate(futureDate.getDate() + days);

    const { data, error } = await supabase
      .from('goals')
      .select('*')
      .lte('deadline', futureDate.toISOString().split('T')[0])
      .eq('completed', false)
      .order('deadline', { ascending: true });

    if (error) {
      console.error('Error fetching upcoming deadlines:', error);
      throw error;
    }

    return data || [];
  }

  // Add a contributor to a goal (only goal owners can do this)
  static async addContributor(goalId: string, contributorEmail: string): Promise<void> {
    // Get the current authenticated user
    const { data: { user }, error: authError } = await supabase.auth.getUser();
    
    if (authError || !user) {
      throw new Error('User not authenticated');
    }

    // Get the user from the public.users table using auth_user_id
    const { data: publicUser, error: userError } = await supabase
      .from('users')
      .select('id')
      .eq('auth_user_id', user.id)
      .single();

    if (userError || !publicUser) {
      throw new Error('User profile not found');
    }

    // Check if the current user is the owner of this goal
    const { data: membership, error: membershipError } = await supabase
      .from('goal_members')
      .select('role')
      .eq('goal_id', goalId)
      .eq('user_id', publicUser.id)
      .single();

    if (membershipError || !membership || membership.role !== 'owner') {
      throw new Error('Only goal owners can add contributors');
    }

    // Find the contributor by email
    const { data: contributor, error: contributorError } = await supabase
      .from('users')
      .select('id')
      .eq('email', contributorEmail)
      .single();

    if (contributorError || !contributor) {
      throw new Error('User not found with that email');
    }

    // Check if contributor is already a member
    const { data: existingMembership, error: existingError } = await supabase
      .from('goal_members')
      .select('id')
      .eq('goal_id', goalId)
      .eq('user_id', contributor.id)
      .single();

    if (existingMembership) {
      throw new Error('User is already a member of this goal');
    }

    // Add the contributor
    const { error: insertError } = await supabase
      .from('goal_members')
      .insert([{
        goal_id: goalId,
        user_id: contributor.id,
        role: 'contributor'
      }]);

    if (insertError) {
      console.error('Error adding contributor:', insertError);
      throw new Error('Failed to add contributor');
    }
  }

  // Remove a member from a goal (only goal owners can do this)
  static async removeMember(goalId: string, memberId: string): Promise<void> {
    // Get the current authenticated user
    const { data: { user }, error: authError } = await supabase.auth.getUser();
    
    if (authError || !user) {
      throw new Error('User not authenticated');
    }

    // Get the user from the public.users table using auth_user_id
    const { data: publicUser, error: userError } = await supabase
      .from('users')
      .select('id')
      .eq('auth_user_id', user.id)
      .single();

    if (userError || !publicUser) {
      throw new Error('User profile not found');
    }

    // Check if the current user is the owner of this goal
    const { data: membership, error: membershipError } = await supabase
      .from('goal_members')
      .select('role')
      .eq('goal_id', goalId)
      .eq('user_id', publicUser.id)
      .single();

    if (membershipError || !membership || membership.role !== 'owner') {
      throw new Error('Only goal owners can remove members');
    }

    // Don't allow owners to remove themselves
    if (memberId === publicUser.id) {
      throw new Error('Goal owners cannot remove themselves');
    }

    // Remove the member
    const { error: deleteError } = await supabase
      .from('goal_members')
      .delete()
      .eq('goal_id', goalId)
      .eq('user_id', memberId);

    if (deleteError) {
      console.error('Error removing member:', deleteError);
      throw new Error('Failed to remove member');
    }
  }

  // Get all members of a specific goal
  static async getGoalMembers(goalId: string): Promise<Array<{
    id: string;
    user_id: string;
    role: string;
    joined_at: string;
    user: {
      id: string;
      name: string;
      email: string;
      avatar?: string;
    };
  }>> {
    // Get the current authenticated user
    const { data: { user }, error: authError } = await supabase.auth.getUser();
    
    if (authError || !user) {
      throw new Error('User not authenticated');
    }

    // Get the user from the public.users table using auth_user_id
    const { data: publicUser, error: userError } = await supabase
      .from('users')
      .select('id')
      .eq('auth_user_id', user.id)
      .single();

    if (userError || !publicUser) {
      throw new Error('User profile not found');
    }

    // Check if the current user is a member of this goal
    const { data: membership, error: membershipError } = await supabase
      .from('goal_members')
      .select('id')
      .eq('goal_id', goalId)
      .eq('user_id', publicUser.id)
      .single();

    if (membershipError || !membership) {
      throw new Error('Access denied: You are not a member of this goal');
    }

    // Get all members of the goal
    const { data: members, error: membersError } = await supabase
      .from('goal_members')
      .select(`
        id,
        user_id,
        role,
        joined_at,
        users (
          id,
          name,
          email,
          avatar
        )
      `)
      .eq('goal_id', goalId)
      .order('joined_at', { ascending: true });

    if (membersError) {
      console.error('Error fetching goal members:', membersError);
      throw new Error('Failed to fetch goal members');
    }

    return (members || []).map(member => ({
      id: member.id,
      user_id: member.user_id,
      role: member.role,
      joined_at: member.joined_at,
      user: member.users
    }));
  }
}

import SQLite from 'react-native-sqlite-storage';
import { TransactionData } from './smsTracker';

// Enable debugging
SQLite.DEBUG(true);
SQLite.enablePromise(true);

export interface StoredTransaction extends TransactionData {
  id: string;
  isUserAdded?: boolean;
  isCounted?: boolean;
  show?: boolean;
  lastModified?: Date;
}

class LocalDatabase {
  private database: SQLite.SQLiteDatabase | null = null;

  async initDatabase(): Promise<void> {
    try {
      this.database = await SQLite.openDatabase({
        name: 'FinanceTracker.db',
        location: 'default',
      });

      await this.createTables();
      console.log('âœ… Database initialized successfully');
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Database initialization failed:', error);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  private async createTables(): Promise<void> {
    if (!this.database) throw new Error('Database not initialized');

    const createTransactionsTable = `
      CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS transactions (
        id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
        amount REAL NOT NULL,
        description TEXT NOT NULL,
        category TEXT NOT NULL,
        date TEXT NOT NULL,
        type TEXT NOT NULL,
        bank TEXT,
        account TEXT,
        isUserAdded INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
        isCounted INTEGER DEFAULT 1,
        show INTEGER DEFAULT 1,
        lastModified TEXT DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
      )
    `;

    const createLastSyncTable = `
      CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS last_sync (
        id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,
        lastMessageDate TEXT,
        lastSyncTime TEXT DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
      )
    `;

    try {
      await this.database.executeSql(createTransactionsTable);
      await this.database.executeSql(createLastSyncTable);
      
      // Add show column to existing transactions table if it doesn't exist
      await this.addShowColumnIfNotExists();
      
      console.log('âœ… Database tables created successfully');
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Table creation failed:', error);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  private async addShowColumnIfNotExists(): Promise<void> {
    if (!this.database) throw new Error('Database not initialized');

    try {
      // Check if show column exists
      const [results] = await this.database.executeSql("PRAGMA table_info(transactions)");
      const columns = [];
      for (let i = 0; i < results.rows.length; i++) {
        columns.push(results.rows.item(i).name);
      }

      if (!columns.includes('show')) {
        console.log('ðŸ”„ Adding show column to transactions table...');
        await this.database.executeSql('ALTER TABLE transactions ADD COLUMN show INTEGER DEFAULT 1');
        console.log('âœ… Show column added successfully');
      } else {
        console.log('âœ… Show column already exists');
      }

      // Update any existing transactions that have NULL show values to 1 (visible)
      const [nullResults] = await this.database.executeSql('SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM transactions WHERE show IS NULL');
      const nullCount = nullResults.rows.item(0).count;
      
      if (nullCount > 0) {
        console.log(`ðŸ”„ Updating ${nullCount} transactions with NULL show values to visible (1)...`);
        await this.database.executeSql('UPDATE transactions SET show = 1 WHERE show IS NULL');
        console.log('âœ… Updated NULL show values to 1');
      }
      
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Failed to add show column:', error);
      // Don't throw error as this is a migration and shouldn't break the app
    }
  }

  // Store a new transaction
  async storeTransaction(transaction: TransactionData, isUserAdded: boolean = false): Promise<void> {
    if (!this.database) throw new Error('Database not initialized');

    // Check if transaction already exists
    const checkQuery = `SELECT id FROM transactions WHERE id = ?`;
    const [existing] = await this.database.executeSql(checkQuery, [transaction.id]);
    
    if (existing.rows.length > 0) {
      console.log('â­ï¸ Transaction already exists:', transaction.id);
      return; // Skip if already exists
    }

    const query = `
      INSERT INTO transactions 
      (id, amount, description, category, date, type, bank, account, isUserAdded, isCounted, show, lastModified)
      VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP)
    `;

    const params = [
      transaction.id,
      transaction.amount,
      transaction.description,
      transaction.category,
      transaction.date.toISOString(),
      transaction.type,
      transaction.bank || null,
      transaction.account || null,
      isUserAdded ? 1 : 0,
      1, // Default to counted
      1  // Default to show = true
    ];

    try {
      console.log('ðŸ’¾ Storing transaction:', {
        id: transaction.id,
        description: transaction.description,
        amount: transaction.amount,
        date: transaction.date.toISOString(),
        type: transaction.type
      });
      
      await this.database.executeSql(query, params);
      console.log('âœ… Transaction stored:', transaction.id);
      
      // Verify storage by checking if it exists
      const verifyQuery = `SELECT * FROM transactions WHERE id = ?`;
      const [verifyResults] = await this.database.executeSql(verifyQuery, [transaction.id]);
      console.log('ðŸ” Verification - transaction exists in DB:', verifyResults.rows.length > 0);
      
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Failed to store transaction:', error);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  // Store multiple transactions
  async storeTransactions(transactions: TransactionData[]): Promise<void> {
    if (!this.database) throw new Error('Database not initialized');

    try {
      await this.database.transaction(async (tx) => {
        for (const transaction of transactions) {
          const query = `
            INSERT OR REPLACE INTO transactions 
            (id, amount, description, category, date, type, bank, account, isUserAdded, isCounted, show, lastModified)
            VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP)
          `;

          const params = [
            transaction.id,
            transaction.amount,
            transaction.description,
            transaction.category,
            transaction.date.toISOString(),
            transaction.type,
            transaction.bank || null,
            transaction.account || null,
            0, // Not user added
            1, // Default to counted
            1  // Default to show = true
          ];

          await tx.executeSql(query, params);
        }
      });
      console.log(`âœ… Stored ${transactions.length} transactions`);
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Failed to store transactions:', error);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  // Get all transactions
  async getAllTransactions(): Promise<StoredTransaction[]> {
    if (!this.database) throw new Error('Database not initialized');

    const query = `SELECT * FROM transactions ORDER BY date DESC`;

    try {
      const [results] = await this.database.executeSql(query);
      console.log('ðŸ” getAllTransactions - rows count:', results.rows.length);
      
      const transactions: StoredTransaction[] = [];

      for (let i = 0; i < results.rows.length; i++) {
        const row = results.rows.item(i);
        console.log(`ðŸ” Transaction ${i + 1}:`, {
          id: row.id,
          description: row.description,
          amount: row.amount,
          date: row.date,
          type: row.type,
          show: row.show
        });
        
        transactions.push({
          id: row.id,
          amount: row.amount,
          description: row.description,
          category: row.category,
          date: new Date(row.date),
          type: row.type,
          bank: row.bank,
          account: row.account,
          isUserAdded: Boolean(row.isUserAdded),
          isCounted: Boolean(row.isCounted),
          show: row.show !== undefined ? Boolean(row.show) : true,
          lastModified: new Date(row.lastModified)
        });
      }

      console.log('ðŸ” getAllTransactions - returning transactions count:', transactions.length);
      return transactions;
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Failed to get transactions:', error);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  // Get transactions for a date range (all transactions, visibility handled in UI)
  async getTransactionsForDateRange(startDate: Date, endDate: Date): Promise<StoredTransaction[]> {
    if (!this.database) throw new Error('Database not initialized');

    const query = `SELECT * FROM transactions WHERE date BETWEEN ? AND ? ORDER BY date DESC`;

    const params = [startDate.toISOString(), endDate.toISOString()];

    try {
      const [results] = await this.database.executeSql(query, params);
      console.log('ðŸ” getTransactionsForDateRange - found', results.rows.length, 'transactions in date range');
      
      const transactions: StoredTransaction[] = [];

      for (let i = 0; i < results.rows.length; i++) {
        const row = results.rows.item(i);
        console.log(`ðŸ” Date range transaction ${i + 1}:`, {
          id: row.id,
          description: row.description,
          show: row.show,
          amount: row.amount,
          date: row.date
        });
        
        transactions.push({
          id: row.id,
          amount: row.amount,
          description: row.description,
          category: row.category,
          date: new Date(row.date),
          type: row.type,
          bank: row.bank,
          account: row.account,
          isUserAdded: Boolean(row.isUserAdded),
          isCounted: Boolean(row.isCounted),
          show: row.show !== undefined ? Boolean(row.show) : true,
          lastModified: new Date(row.lastModified)
        });
      }

      return transactions;
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Failed to get transactions for date range:', error);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  // Get only counted transactions (all counted transactions, visibility handled in UI)
  async getCountedTransactions(): Promise<StoredTransaction[]> {
    if (!this.database) throw new Error('Database not initialized');

    const query = `SELECT * FROM transactions WHERE isCounted = 1`;

    try {
      const [results] = await this.database.executeSql(query);
      console.log('ðŸ” getCountedTransactions - found', results.rows.length, 'counted transactions');
      
      const transactions: StoredTransaction[] = [];

      for (let i = 0; i < results.rows.length; i++) {
        const row = results.rows.item(i);
        transactions.push({
          id: row.id,
          amount: row.amount,
          description: row.description,
          category: row.category,
          date: new Date(row.date),
          type: row.type,
          bank: row.bank,
          account: row.account,
          isUserAdded: Boolean(row.isUserAdded),
          isCounted: Boolean(row.isCounted),
          show: row.show !== undefined ? Boolean(row.show) : true,
          lastModified: new Date(row.lastModified)
        });
      }

      return transactions;
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Failed to get counted transactions:', error);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  // Get only visible transactions (where show = true)
  async getVisibleTransactions(): Promise<StoredTransaction[]> {
    if (!this.database) throw new Error('Database not initialized');

    const query = `SELECT * FROM transactions WHERE show = 1 ORDER BY date DESC`;

    try {
      const [results] = await this.database.executeSql(query);
      console.log('ðŸ” getVisibleTransactions - found', results.rows.length, 'visible transactions');
      
      const transactions: StoredTransaction[] = [];

      for (let i = 0; i < results.rows.length; i++) {
        const row = results.rows.item(i);
        console.log(`ðŸ” Visible transaction ${i + 1}:`, {
          id: row.id,
          description: row.description,
          show: row.show,
          amount: row.amount
        });
        
        transactions.push({
          id: row.id,
          amount: row.amount,
          description: row.description,
          category: row.category,
          date: new Date(row.date),
          type: row.type,
          bank: row.bank,
          account: row.account,
          isUserAdded: Boolean(row.isUserAdded),
          isCounted: Boolean(row.isCounted),
          show: row.show !== undefined ? Boolean(row.show) : true,
          lastModified: new Date(row.lastModified)
        });
      }

      return transactions;
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Failed to get visible transactions:', error);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  // Update transaction (for user edits)
  async updateTransaction(transaction: StoredTransaction): Promise<void> {
    if (!this.database) throw new Error('Database not initialized');

    const query = `
      UPDATE transactions 
      SET amount = ?, description = ?, category = ?, date = ?, type = ?, 
          bank = ?, account = ?, isUserAdded = ?, isCounted = ?, show = ?, lastModified = CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
      WHERE id = ?
    `;

    const params = [
        transaction.amount,
        transaction.description,
        transaction.category,
      transaction.date.toISOString(),
      transaction.type,
      transaction.bank || null,
      transaction.account || null,
      transaction.isUserAdded ? 1 : 0,
      transaction.isCounted ? 1 : 0,
      transaction.show !== undefined ? (transaction.show ? 1 : 0) : 1,
      transaction.id
    ];

    try {
      await this.database.executeSql(query, params);
      console.log('âœ… Transaction updated:', transaction.id);
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Failed to update transaction:', error);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  // Toggle transaction counted status
  async toggleTransactionCounted(id: string): Promise<void> {
    if (!this.database) throw new Error('Database not initialized');

    const query = `
      UPDATE transactions 
      SET isCounted = CASE WHEN isCounted = 1 THEN 0 ELSE 1 END,
          lastModified = CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
      WHERE id = ?
    `;

    try {
      await this.database.executeSql(query, [id]);
      console.log('âœ… Transaction counted status toggled:', id);
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Failed to toggle transaction counted status:', error);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  // Toggle transaction show status
  async toggleTransactionShow(id: string): Promise<void> {
    if (!this.database) throw new Error('Database not initialized');

    // First, get the current show status
    const getQuery = `SELECT show FROM transactions WHERE id = ?`;
    const [currentResult] = await this.database.executeSql(getQuery, [id]);
    
    if (currentResult.rows.length === 0) {
      throw new Error('Transaction not found');
    }
    
    const currentShow = currentResult.rows.item(0).show;
    const newShow = currentShow === 1 ? 0 : 1;
    
    console.log(`ðŸ”„ Toggling transaction ${id} show from ${currentShow} to ${newShow}`);

    const updateQuery = `
      UPDATE transactions 
      SET show = ?,
          lastModified = CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
      WHERE id = ?
    `;

    try {
      await this.database.executeSql(updateQuery, [newShow, id]);
      console.log('âœ… Transaction show status toggled:', id, 'from', currentShow, 'to', newShow);
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Failed to toggle transaction show status:', error);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  // Delete transaction
  async deleteTransaction(id: string): Promise<void> {
    if (!this.database) throw new Error('Database not initialized');

    const query = `DELETE FROM transactions WHERE id = ?`;

    try {
      await this.database.executeSql(query, [id]);
      console.log('âœ… Transaction deleted:', id);
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Failed to delete transaction:', error);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  // Clear all transactions
  async clearAllTransactions(): Promise<void> {
    if (!this.database) throw new Error('Database not initialized');

    const query = `DELETE FROM transactions`;

    try {
      await this.database.executeSql(query);
      console.log('ðŸ—‘ï¸ All transactions cleared');
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Failed to clear transactions:', error);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  // Get last sync date
  async getLastSyncDate(): Promise<Date | null> {
    if (!this.database) throw new Error('Database not initialized');

    const query = `SELECT lastMessageDate FROM last_sync ORDER BY id DESC LIMIT 1`;

    try {
      const [results] = await this.database.executeSql(query);
      console.log('ðŸ” getLastSyncDate - rows count:', results.rows.length);
      if (results.rows.length > 0) {
        const row = results.rows.item(0);
        console.log('ðŸ” getLastSyncDate - row data:', row);
        const lastDate = row.lastMessageDate;
        console.log('ðŸ” getLastSyncDate - lastDate:', lastDate);
        return lastDate ? new Date(lastDate) : null;
      }
      console.log('ðŸ” getLastSyncDate - no rows found');
      return null;
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Failed to get last sync date:', error);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  // Update last sync date
  async updateLastSyncDate(lastMessageDate: Date): Promise<void> {
    if (!this.database) throw new Error('Database not initialized');

    const query = `
      INSERT OR REPLACE INTO last_sync (id, lastMessageDate, lastSyncTime)
      VALUES (1, ?, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP)
    `;

    try {
      console.log('ðŸ“… updateLastSyncDate - inserting date:', lastMessageDate.toISOString());
      await this.database.executeSql(query, [lastMessageDate.toISOString()]);
      console.log('âœ… Last sync date updated:', lastMessageDate);
      
      // Verify the insertion
      const verifyQuery = `SELECT * FROM last_sync WHERE id = 1`;
      const [verifyResults] = await this.database.executeSql(verifyQuery);
      console.log('ðŸ” Verification - rows count:', verifyResults.rows.length);
      if (verifyResults.rows.length > 0) {
        const row = verifyResults.rows.item(0);
        console.log('ðŸ” Verification - row data:', row);
      }
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Failed to update last sync date:', error);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  // Get database statistics
  async getDatabaseStats(): Promise<{
    totalTransactions: number;
    countedTransactions: number;
    userAddedTransactions: number;
    visibleTransactions: number;
    lastSyncDate: Date | null;
  }> {
    if (!this.database) throw new Error('Database not initialized');

    try {
      const [totalResult] = await this.database.executeSql('SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM transactions');
      const [countedResult] = await this.database.executeSql('SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM transactions WHERE isCounted = 1');
      const [userAddedResult] = await this.database.executeSql('SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM transactions WHERE isUserAdded = 1');
      const [visibleResult] = await this.database.executeSql('SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM transactions WHERE show = 1');
      
      // Check last_sync table
      const [lastSyncResult] = await this.database.executeSql('SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM last_sync');
      console.log('ðŸ” Database stats - last_sync table rows:', lastSyncResult.rows.item(0).count);
      
      const lastSyncDate = await this.getLastSyncDate();

      return {
        totalTransactions: totalResult.rows.item(0).count,
        countedTransactions: countedResult.rows.item(0).count,
        userAddedTransactions: userAddedResult.rows.item(0).count,
        visibleTransactions: visibleResult.rows.item(0).count,
        lastSyncDate
      };
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Failed to get database stats:', error);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  // Debug method to check show values
  async debugShowValues(): Promise<void> {
    if (!this.database) throw new Error('Database not initialized');

    try {
      console.log('ðŸ” Debugging show values...');
      
      // Get all transactions with their show values
      const [results] = await this.database.executeSql('SELECT id, description, show FROM transactions');
      console.log('ðŸ“Š Total transactions in database:', results.rows.length);
      
      for (let i = 0; i < results.rows.length; i++) {
        const row = results.rows.item(i);
        console.log(`Transaction ${i + 1}: ID=${row.id}, Show=${row.show}, Description=${row.description}`);
      }
      
      // Count visible vs hidden
      const [visibleCount] = await this.database.executeSql('SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM transactions WHERE show = 1');
      const [hiddenCount] = await this.database.executeSql('SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM transactions WHERE show = 0');
      const [nullCount] = await this.database.executeSql('SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM transactions WHERE show IS NULL');
      
      console.log('ðŸ“Š Show values summary:');
      console.log('  - Visible (show=1):', visibleCount.rows.item(0).count);
      console.log('  - Hidden (show=0):', hiddenCount.rows.item(0).count);
      console.log('  - Null (show=NULL):', nullCount.rows.item(0).count);
      
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Error debugging show values:', error);
    }
  }

  // Force fix show values for all transactions
  async fixShowValues(): Promise<void> {
    if (!this.database) throw new Error('Database not initialized');

    try {
      console.log('ðŸ”§ Fixing show values for all transactions...');
      
      // Update any NULL values to 1 (visible)
      const [nullResults] = await this.database.executeSql('SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM transactions WHERE show IS NULL');
      const nullCount = nullResults.rows.item(0).count;
      
      if (nullCount > 0) {
        console.log(`ðŸ”„ Updating ${nullCount} transactions with NULL show values to visible (1)...`);
        await this.database.executeSql('UPDATE transactions SET show = 1 WHERE show IS NULL');
        console.log('âœ… Updated NULL show values to 1');
      }
      
      // Update any undefined values to 1 (visible)
      const [undefinedResults] = await this.database.executeSql('SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM transactions WHERE show IS NOT 0 AND show IS NOT 1');
      const undefinedCount = undefinedResults.rows.item(0).count;
      
      if (undefinedCount > 0) {
        console.log(`ðŸ”„ Updating ${undefinedCount} transactions with undefined show values to visible (1)...`);
        await this.database.executeSql('UPDATE transactions SET show = 1 WHERE show IS NOT 0 AND show IS NOT 1');
        console.log('âœ… Updated undefined show values to 1');
      }
      
      console.log('âœ… Show values fixed successfully');
      
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Error fixing show values:', error);
    }
  }

  // Close database
  async closeDatabase(): Promise<void> {
    if (this.database) {
      await this.database.close();
      this.database = null;
      console.log('âœ… Database closed');
    }
  }
}

export default new LocalDatabase();

import { oneSignalService, NotificationData } from './oneSignal';
import { supabase } from './supabase';

export class NotificationManager {
  private static instance: NotificationManager;

  static getInstance(): NotificationManager {
    if (!NotificationManager.instance) {
      NotificationManager.instance = new NotificationManager();
    }
    return NotificationManager.instance;
  }

  // Initialize notifications for a user
  async initializeUser(userId: string, userData: any): Promise<void> {
    try {
      // Set user properties in OneSignal
      await oneSignalService.setUserProperties({
        userId,
        rank: userData.rank || 'Novice',
        streak: userData.streak || 0,
        xp: userData.xp || 0
      });

      // Set up user preferences
      await this.setupUserPreferences(userId);
      
      console.log('âœ… User notifications initialized');
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Error initializing user notifications:', error);
    }
  }

  // Set up user notification preferences
  private async setupUserPreferences(userId: string): Promise<void> {
    try {
      const { data, error } = await supabase
        .from('users')
        .select('notification_preferences')
        .eq('id', userId)
        .single();

      if (error) throw error;

      // Set default preferences if none exist
      if (!data?.notification_preferences) {
        const defaultPreferences = {
          daily_challenge: true,
          friend_requests: true,
          quiz_reminders: true,
          streak_warnings: true,
          level_up: true
        };

        await supabase
          .from('users')
          .update({ notification_preferences: defaultPreferences })
          .eq('id', userId);
      }
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Error setting up user preferences:', error);
    }
  }

  // Send daily challenge notification
  async sendDailyChallengeNotification(userId: string): Promise<void> {
    const notification: NotificationData = {
      type: 'daily_challenge',
      title: 'ðŸŽ¯ Daily Challenge is Here!',
      message: 'Your new daily quiz is ready. Test your financial knowledge!',
      data: { userId }
    };

    await this.sendNotification(userId, notification);
  }

  // Send friend request notification
  async sendFriendRequestNotification(userId: string, requesterName: string): Promise<void> {
    const notification: NotificationData = {
      type: 'friend_request',
      title: 'ðŸ‘¥ New Friend Request',
      message: `${requesterName} wants to be your friend!`,
      data: { userId, requesterName }
    };

    await this.sendNotification(userId, notification);
  }

  // Send quiz reminder notification
  async sendQuizReminderNotification(userId: string): Promise<void> {
    const notification: NotificationData = {
      type: 'quiz_reminder',
      title: 'ðŸ“š Time for a Quiz!',
      message: 'Keep your streak alive! Take a quick quiz now.',
      data: { userId }
    };

    await this.sendNotification(userId, notification);
  }

  // Send streak warning notification
  async sendStreakWarningNotification(userId: string, currentStreak: number): Promise<void> {
    const notification: NotificationData = {
      type: 'streak_warning',
      title: 'âš ï¸ Streak at Risk!',
      message: `Your ${currentStreak}-day streak is about to break! Complete a lesson today.`,
      data: { userId, currentStreak }
    };

    await this.sendNotification(userId, notification);
  }

  // Send level up notification
  async sendLevelUpNotification(userId: string, newRank: string): Promise<void> {
    const notification: NotificationData = {
      type: 'level_up',
      title: 'ðŸŽ‰ Level Up!',
      message: `Congratulations! You've reached ${newRank} level!`,
      data: { userId, newRank }
    };

    await this.sendNotification(userId, notification);
  }

  // Send notification to specific user
  private async sendNotification(userId: string, notification: NotificationData): Promise<void> {
    try {
      // Check if user has notifications enabled
      const { data: userData, error } = await supabase
        .from('users')
        .select('notification_preferences')
        .eq('id', userId)
        .single();

      if (error) throw error;

      const preferences = userData?.notification_preferences || {};
      const notificationType = notification.type as keyof typeof preferences;

      // Check if this type of notification is enabled
      if (preferences[notificationType] === false) {
        console.log(`ðŸ”‡ Notifications disabled for ${notificationType}`);
        return;
      }

      // Send via OneSignal (this would typically be done from your backend)
      await oneSignalService.sendNotificationToUser(userId, notification);

      // Log notification in Supabase for tracking
      await this.logNotification(userId, notification);

      console.log(`âœ… Notification sent to user ${userId}: ${notification.title}`);
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Error sending notification:', error);
    }
  }

  // Log notification in database
  private async logNotification(userId: string, notification: NotificationData): Promise<void> {
    try {
      await supabase
        .from('notification_logs')
        .insert({
          user_id: userId,
          type: notification.type,
          title: notification.title,
          message: notification.message,
          sent_at: new Date().toISOString()
        });
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Error logging notification:', error);
    }
  }

  // Schedule daily challenge notification
  async scheduleDailyChallengeNotification(userId: string, hour: number = 9): Promise<void> {
    try {
      const now = new Date();
      const targetTime = new Date(now);
      targetTime.setHours(hour, 0, 0, 0);

      // If it's already past today's target time, schedule for tomorrow
      if (now > targetTime) {
        targetTime.setDate(targetTime.getDate() + 1);
      }

      const delaySeconds = Math.floor((targetTime.getTime() - now.getTime()) / 1000);

      const notification: NotificationData = {
        type: 'daily_challenge',
        title: 'ðŸŽ¯ Daily Challenge is Here!',
        message: 'Your new daily quiz is ready. Test your financial knowledge!',
        data: { userId }
      };

      await oneSignalService.scheduleNotification(notification, delaySeconds);
      console.log(`âœ… Daily challenge notification scheduled for ${targetTime.toLocaleString()}`);
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Error scheduling daily challenge notification:', error);
    }
  }

  // Schedule streak warning notification (send at 8 PM if no activity)
  async scheduleStreakWarningNotification(userId: string): Promise<void> {
    try {
      const now = new Date();
      const targetTime = new Date(now);
      targetTime.setHours(20, 0, 0, 0); // 8 PM

      // If it's already past 8 PM, schedule for tomorrow
      if (now > targetTime) {
        targetTime.setDate(targetTime.getDate() + 1);
      }

      const delaySeconds = Math.floor((targetTime.getTime() - now.getTime()) / 1000);

      const notification: NotificationData = {
        type: 'streak_warning',
        title: 'âš ï¸ Streak at Risk!',
        message: 'Complete a lesson today to keep your streak alive!',
        data: { userId }
      };

      await oneSignalService.scheduleNotification(notification, delaySeconds);
      console.log(`âœ… Streak warning notification scheduled for ${targetTime.toLocaleString()}`);
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Error scheduling streak warning notification:', error);
    }
  }

  // Update user notification preferences
  async updateUserPreferences(userId: string, preferences: Record<string, boolean>): Promise<void> {
    try {
      await supabase
        .from('users')
        .update({ notification_preferences: preferences })
        .eq('id', userId);

      console.log('âœ… User notification preferences updated');
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Error updating user preferences:', error);
    }
  }

  // Get user notification preferences
  async getUserPreferences(userId: string): Promise<Record<string, boolean> | null> {
    try {
      const { data, error } = await supabase
        .from('users')
        .select('notification_preferences')
        .eq('id', userId)
        .single();

      if (error) throw error;
      return data?.notification_preferences || null;
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Error getting user preferences:', error);
      return null;
    }
  }
}

// Export singleton instance
export const notificationManager = NotificationManager.getInstance();

FILE: services/privacyCompliantSmsTracker.ts
================================================
import { Platform } from 'react-native';
import { check, request, PERMISSIONS, RESULTS } from 'react-native-permissions';
import expenseDetector from './expenseDetector';
import localDatabase from './localDatabase';
import { TransactionData, SmsMessage } from './smsTracker';
import { LocalTransaction } from './localDatabase';

// For Android SMS reading
let SmsAndroid: any = null;
if (Platform.OS === 'android') {
  try {
    SmsAndroid = require('react-native-get-sms-android');
  } catch (error) {
    console.log('SMS module not available');
  }
}

class PrivacyCompliantSmsTracker {
  private hasPermission: boolean = false;
  private isProcessing: boolean = false;
  private isInitialized: boolean = false;

  async initialize(): Promise<void> {
    if (this.isInitialized) return;
    
    try {
      await localDatabase.initialize();
      this.isInitialized = true;
      console.log('Privacy-compliant SMS tracker initialized');
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Error initializing privacy-compliant SMS tracker:', error);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  async requestSmsPermission(): Promise<boolean> {
    if (Platform.OS !== 'android') {
      console.log('SMS tracking is only available on Android');
      return false;
    }

    try {
      const result = await check(PERMISSIONS.ANDROID.READ_SMS);
      
      if (result === RESULTS.GRANTED) {
        this.hasPermission = true;
        return true;
      }

      if (result === RESULTS.DENIED) {
        const permissionResult = await request(PERMISSIONS.ANDROID.READ_SMS);
        this.hasPermission = permissionResult === RESULTS.GRANTED;
        return this.hasPermission;
      }

      return false;
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Error requesting SMS permission:', error);
      return false;
    }
  }

  async getAllSms(): Promise<SmsMessage[]> {
    if (!this.hasPermission || Platform.OS !== 'android' || !SmsAndroid) {
      return [];
    }

    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
      const timeout = setTimeout(() => {
        reject(new Error('SMS reading timeout'));
      }, 10000);

      SmsAndroid.list(
        JSON.stringify({
          box: 'inbox',
          maxCount: 1000,
        }),
        (fail: any) => {
          clearTimeout(timeout);
          console.error('Failed to get SMS:', fail);
          reject(fail);
        },
        (count: number, smsList: string) => {
          clearTimeout(timeout);
          try {
            const messages: SmsMessage[] = JSON.parse(smsList);
            resolve(messages);
          } catch (error) {
            console.error('Error parsing SMS list:', error);
            reject(error);
          }
        }
      );
    });
  }

  // Process SMS messages locally and store only processed data
  async processAndStoreSmsLocally(): Promise<LocalTransaction[]> {
    if (!this.isInitialized) {
      await this.initialize();
    }

    try {
      // Get unprocessed SMS messages from local database
      const unprocessedSms = await localDatabase.getUnprocessedSmsMessages();
      
      if (unprocessedSms.length === 0) {
        console.log('No unprocessed SMS messages found');
        return [];
      }

      // Convert to SmsMessage format for processing
      const smsMessages: SmsMessage[] = unprocessedSms.map(sms => ({
        id: sms.id,
        address: sms.address,
        body: sms.body,
        date: sms.date,
        type: sms.type
      }));

      // Process SMS locally using expense detector
      const transactions = expenseDetector.detectExpenses(smsMessages);
      
      // Store processed transactions locally
      const storedTransactions: LocalTransaction[] = [];
      
      for (const transaction of transactions) {
        const localTransaction: LocalTransaction = {
          id: transaction.id,
          amount: transaction.amount,
          description: transaction.description,
          category: transaction.category,
          merchant: transaction.bank, // Using bank as merchant for now
          bank: transaction.bank,
          account: transaction.account,
          transaction_type: transaction.type,
          currency: 'INR',
          date: transaction.date.toISOString(),
          sms_id: transaction.id,
          created_at: new Date().toISOString(),
          updated_at: new Date().toISOString()
        };

        await localDatabase.saveTransaction(localTransaction);
        await localDatabase.markSmsAsProcessed(transaction.id, transaction.id);
        storedTransactions.push(localTransaction);
      }

      console.log(`Processed and stored ${storedTransactions.length} transactions locally`);
      return storedTransactions;

    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Error processing SMS locally:', error);
      return [];
    }
  }

  // Sync new SMS messages to local database
  async syncNewSmsMessages(): Promise<void> {
    if (!this.hasPermission) {
      console.log('SMS permission not granted');
      return;
    }

    try {
      // Get all SMS from device
      const deviceSms = await this.getAllSms();
      console.log(`Found ${deviceSms.length} SMS messages on device`);

      // Save all SMS to local database (this is safe as it's local only)
      await localDatabase.saveSmsMessages(deviceSms);
      console.log('SMS messages saved to local database');

      // Process unprocessed messages
      await this.processAndStoreSmsLocally();

    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Error syncing SMS messages:', error);
    }
  }

  // Get transactions from local database
  async getTransactions(dateRange?: { start: string; end: string }): Promise<LocalTransaction[]> {
    if (!this.isInitialized) {
      await this.initialize();
    }

    return localDatabase.getTransactions(dateRange);
  }

  // Get transaction statistics
  async getTransactionStats(dateRange?: { start: string; end: string }): Promise<{
    totalSpent: number;
    totalReceived: number;
    categoryBreakdown: { category: string; amount: number }[];
  }> {
    if (!this.isInitialized) {
      await this.initialize();
    }

    return localDatabase.getTransactionStats(dateRange);
  }

  // Get transactions by category
  async getTransactionsByCategory(category: string): Promise<LocalTransaction[]> {
    if (!this.isInitialized) {
      await this.initialize();
    }

    return localDatabase.getTransactionsByCategory(category);
  }

  // Get recent transactions (last 30 days)
  async getRecentTransactions(): Promise<LocalTransaction[]> {
    const thirtyDaysAgo = new Date();
    thirtyDaysAgo.setDate(thirtyDaysAgo.getDate() - 30);

    return this.getTransactions({
      start: thirtyDaysAgo.toISOString(),
      end: new Date().toISOString()
    });
  }

  // Get transactions for a specific month and year
  async getTransactionsForMonth(year: number, month: number): Promise<LocalTransaction[]> {
    const startDate = new Date(year, month - 1, 1);
    const endDate = new Date(year, month, 0);
    endDate.setHours(23, 59, 59, 999);

    return this.getTransactions({
      start: startDate.toISOString(),
      end: endDate.toISOString()
    });
  }

  // Get transactions for a specific year
  async getTransactionsForYear(year: number): Promise<LocalTransaction[]> {
    const startDate = new Date(year, 0, 1);
    const endDate = new Date(year, 11, 31);
    endDate.setHours(23, 59, 59, 999);

    return this.getTransactions({
      start: startDate.toISOString(),
      end: endDate.toISOString()
    });
  }

  // Get transactions for current week (Monday to Sunday)
  async getTransactionsForCurrentWeek(): Promise<LocalTransaction[]> {
    const now = new Date();
    const startOfWeek = new Date(now);
    const dayOfWeek = now.getDay();
    const diff = now.getDate() - dayOfWeek + (dayOfWeek === 0 ? -6 : 1);
    startOfWeek.setDate(diff);
    startOfWeek.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0);
    
    const endOfWeek = new Date(startOfWeek);
    endOfWeek.setDate(startOfWeek.getDate() + 6);
    endOfWeek.setHours(23, 59, 59, 999);
    
    return this.getTransactions({
      start: startOfWeek.toISOString(),
      end: endOfWeek.toISOString()
    });
  }

  // Export data for backup (privacy-compliant)
  async exportData(): Promise<{
    transactions: LocalTransaction[];
    goals: any[];
    settings: any;
  }> {
    if (!this.isInitialized) {
      await this.initialize();
    }

    return localDatabase.exportData();
  }

  // Import data from backup
  async importData(data: {
    transactions: LocalTransaction[];
    goals: any[];
    settings: any;
  }): Promise<void> {
    if (!this.isInitialized) {
      await this.initialize();
    }

    await localDatabase.importData(data);
  }

  // Clear all local data (for privacy)
  async clearAllData(): Promise<void> {
    if (!this.isInitialized) {
      await this.initialize();
    }

    await localDatabase.clearAllData();
  }

  // Get categories from local database
  async getCategories(): Promise<any[]> {
    if (!this.isInitialized) {
      await this.initialize();
    }

    return localDatabase.getCategories();
  }

  // Get goals from local database
  async getGoals(): Promise<any[]> {
    if (!this.isInitialized) {
      await this.initialize();
    }

    return localDatabase.getGoals();
  }

  // Save goal to local database
  async saveGoal(goal: any): Promise<void> {
    if (!this.isInitialized) {
      await this.initialize();
    }

    await localDatabase.saveGoal(goal);
  }

  // Get settings from local database
  async getSettings(): Promise<any> {
    if (!this.isInitialized) {
      await this.initialize();
    }

    return localDatabase.getSettings();
  }

  // Update settings in local database
  async updateSettings(settings: Partial<any>): Promise<void> {
    if (!this.isInitialized) {
      await this.initialize();
    }

    await localDatabase.updateSettings(settings);
  }

  // Check if SMS tracking is enabled
  async isSmsTrackingEnabled(): Promise<boolean> {
    const settings = await this.getSettings();
    return settings.sms_tracking_enabled;
  }

  // Toggle SMS tracking
  async toggleSmsTracking(enabled: boolean): Promise<void> {
    await this.updateSettings({ sms_tracking_enabled: enabled });
  }
}

export default new PrivacyCompliantSmsTracker();

FILE: services/smsTracker.ts
