import { Platform } from 'react-native';
import { check, request, PERMISSIONS, RESULTS } from 'react-native-permissions';
import expenseDetector from './expenseDetector';

// For Android SMS reading
let SmsAndroid: any = null;
if (Platform.OS === 'android') {
  try {
    SmsAndroid = require('react-native-get-sms-android');
  } catch (error) {
    console.log('SMS module not available');
  }
}

export interface TransactionData {
  id: string;
  amount: number;
  description: string;
  category: string;
  date: Date;
  type: 'credit' | 'debit';
  bank?: string;
  account?: string;
}

export interface SmsMessage {
  id: string;
  address: string;
  body: string;
  date: number;
  type: string;
}

class SmsTracker {
  private hasPermission: boolean = false;
  private isProcessing: boolean = false;

  async requestSmsPermission(): Promise<boolean> {
    console.log('ðŸ” Requesting SMS permission...');
    
    if (Platform.OS !== 'android') {
      console.log('âŒ SMS tracking is only available on Android');
      return false;
    }

    try {
      const result = await check(PERMISSIONS.ANDROID.READ_SMS);
      console.log('ðŸ” Permission check result:', result);
      
      if (result === RESULTS.GRANTED) {
        this.hasPermission = true;
        console.log('âœ… SMS permission already granted');
        return true;
      }

      if (result === RESULTS.DENIED) {
        console.log('ðŸ” Requesting permission...');
        const permissionResult = await request(PERMISSIONS.ANDROID.READ_SMS);
        console.log('ðŸ” Permission request result:', permissionResult);
        this.hasPermission = permissionResult === RESULTS.GRANTED;
        return this.hasPermission;
      }

      console.log('âŒ Permission not available');
      return false;
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Error requesting SMS permission:', error);
      return false;
    }
  }

  async getAllSms(): Promise<SmsMessage[]> {
    console.log('ðŸ” getAllSms called');
    console.log('ðŸ“± Platform:', Platform.OS);
    console.log('ðŸ“± SmsAndroid available:', !!SmsAndroid);
    console.log('ðŸ“± Has permission:', this.hasPermission);
    
    if (!this.hasPermission || Platform.OS !== 'android' || !SmsAndroid) {
      console.log('âŒ Cannot read SMS - missing permission or module');
      return [];
    }

    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
      console.log('ðŸ“± Starting SMS read...');
      
      // Add timeout to prevent hanging
      const timeout = setTimeout(() => {
        console.log('â° SMS reading timeout');
        reject(new Error('SMS reading timeout'));
      }, 10000); // 10 second timeout

      const params = {
        box: 'inbox',
        maxCount: 1000, // Reduced to 1000 messages
      };
      
      console.log('ðŸ“± SMS params:', JSON.stringify(params));

      SmsAndroid.list(
        JSON.stringify(params),
        (fail: any) => {
          clearTimeout(timeout);
          console.error('âŒ Failed to get SMS:', fail);
          reject(fail);
        },
        (count: number, smsList: string) => {
          clearTimeout(timeout);
          console.log('ðŸ“± SMS read success - count:', count);
          console.log('ðŸ“± SMS list length:', smsList.length);
          
          try {
            const messages: SmsMessage[] = JSON.parse(smsList);
            console.log('ðŸ“± Parsed messages count:', messages.length);
            resolve(messages);
          } catch (error) {
            console.error('âŒ Error parsing SMS list:', error);
            reject(error);
          }
        }
      );
    });
  }

  // Extract financial transactions from SMS messages
  async extractTransactions(messages: SmsMessage[]): Promise<TransactionData[]> {
    try {
      // Process all messages to get complete data
      return await expenseDetector.detectExpenses(messages);
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Error extracting transactions:', error);
      return [];
    }
  }

  // Get recent transactions (last 30 days)
  async getRecentTransactions(): Promise<TransactionData[]> {
    if (this.isProcessing) {
      return [];
    }
    
    this.isProcessing = true;
    try {
      const messages = await this.getAllSms();
      const thirtyDaysAgo = Date.now() - (30 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000);
      
      const recentMessages = messages.filter(msg => msg.date > thirtyDaysAgo);
      return await this.extractTransactions(recentMessages);
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Error getting recent transactions:', error);
      return [];
    } finally {
      this.isProcessing = false;
    }
  }

  // Get transactions for a specific date range
  async getTransactionsForDateRange(startDate: Date, endDate: Date): Promise<TransactionData[]> {
    console.log('getTransactionsForDateRange called');
    
    if (this.isProcessing) {
      console.log('isProcessing is true, resetting...');
      this.isProcessing = false;
    }
    
    this.isProcessing = true;
    try {
      console.log('Getting SMS messages for date range...');
      const messages = await this.getAllSms();
      console.log('Total SMS messages:', messages.length);
      
      const startTime = startDate.getTime();
      const endTime = endDate.getTime();
      
      const filteredMessages = messages.filter(msg => 
        msg.date >= startTime && msg.date <= endTime
      );
      
      console.log('Filtered messages for date range:', filteredMessages.length);
      console.log('Date range:', new Date(startTime).toISOString(), 'to', new Date(endTime).toISOString());
      
      const transactions = await this.extractTransactions(filteredMessages);
      console.log('Extracted transactions for date range:', transactions.length);
      
      return transactions;
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Error getting transactions for date range:', error);
      return [];
    } finally {
      this.isProcessing = false;
    }
  }

  // Get transactions for a specific month and year
  async getTransactionsForMonth(year: number, month: number): Promise<TransactionData[]> {
    const startDate = new Date(year, month - 1, 1); // month is 0-indexed
    const endDate = new Date(year, month, 0); // Last day of the month
    endDate.setHours(23, 59, 59, 999); // End of day
    
    return this.getTransactionsForDateRange(startDate, endDate);
  }

  // Get transactions for a specific year
  async getTransactionsForYear(year: number): Promise<TransactionData[]> {
    console.log('getTransactionsForYear called for year:', year);
    
    if (this.isProcessing) {
      console.log('isProcessing is true, resetting...');
      this.isProcessing = false;
    }
    
    const startDate = new Date(year, 0, 1); // January 1st
    const endDate = new Date(year, 11, 31); // December 31st
    endDate.setHours(23, 59, 59, 999); // End of day
    
    console.log('Date range:', startDate.toISOString(), 'to', endDate.toISOString());
    
    return this.getTransactionsForDateRange(startDate, endDate);
  }

  // Get transactions for current week (Monday to Sunday)
  async getTransactionsForCurrentWeek(): Promise<TransactionData[]> {
    const now = new Date();
    const startOfWeek = new Date(now);
    const dayOfWeek = now.getDay();
    const diff = now.getDate() - dayOfWeek + (dayOfWeek === 0 ? -6 : 1); // Adjust for Sunday
    startOfWeek.setDate(diff);
    startOfWeek.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0);
    
    const endOfWeek = new Date(startOfWeek);
    endOfWeek.setDate(startOfWeek.getDate() + 6);
    endOfWeek.setHours(23, 59, 59, 999);
    
    return this.getTransactionsForDateRange(startOfWeek, endOfWeek);
  }

  // Get all transactions (no date filtering)
  async getAllTransactions(): Promise<TransactionData[]> {
    console.log('getAllTransactions called, isProcessing:', this.isProcessing);
    
    // Reset isProcessing if it's been stuck
    if (this.isProcessing) {
      console.log('Resetting isProcessing flag');
      this.isProcessing = false;
    }
    
    this.isProcessing = true;
    try {
      console.log('Getting all SMS messages...');
      const messages = await this.getAllSms();
      console.log('SMS messages count:', messages.length);
      
      const transactions = await this.extractTransactions(messages);
      console.log('Extracted transactions count:', transactions.length);
      
      return transactions;
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Error getting all transactions:', error);
      return [];
    } finally {
      this.isProcessing = false;
      console.log('getAllTransactions completed, isProcessing reset to false');
    }
  }
}

export default new SmsTracker();

FILE: supabase/functions/calculate-streak.sql
================================================
-- Simple streak calculation using existing user_progress table
-- This function calculates streak based on consecutive days with quiz completions

CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION calculate_user_streak(user_uuid UUID)
RETURNS INTEGER AS $$
DECLARE
  current_streak INTEGER := 0;
  check_date DATE;
  has_quiz_completion BOOLEAN;
BEGIN
  -- Start from yesterday and work backwards (don't count today until user completes something)
  check_date := CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '1 day';
  
  -- Count consecutive days with quiz completions
  WHILE true LOOP
    -- Check if user completed any quiz on this date
    SELECT EXISTS(
      SELECT 1 FROM user_progress 
      WHERE user_id = user_uuid 
      AND quiz_completed = true
      AND DATE(quiz_completed_at) = check_date
    ) INTO has_quiz_completion;
    
    IF has_quiz_completion THEN
      current_streak := current_streak + 1;
      check_date := check_date - INTERVAL '1 day';
    ELSE
      -- No quiz completion on this day, streak breaks
      EXIT;
    END IF;
    
    -- Safety check to prevent infinite loop
    IF check_date < CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '365 days' THEN
      EXIT;
    END IF;
  END LOOP;
  
  RETURN current_streak;
END;
$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql;

-- Function to check and update streak (call this when user opens app)
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION check_and_update_streak(user_uuid UUID)
RETURNS INTEGER AS $$
DECLARE
  calculated_streak INTEGER;
  has_completed_today BOOLEAN;
BEGIN
  -- Check if user has completed a quiz today
  SELECT EXISTS(
    SELECT 1 FROM user_progress 
    WHERE user_id = user_uuid 
    AND quiz_completed = true
    AND DATE(quiz_completed_at) = CURRENT_DATE
  ) INTO has_completed_today;
  
  -- Calculate base streak (yesterday and before)
  calculated_streak := calculate_user_streak(user_uuid);
  
  -- If user completed something today, add 1 to streak
  IF has_completed_today THEN
    calculated_streak := calculated_streak + 1;
  END IF;
  
  -- Update user's streak in database
  UPDATE users 
  SET 
    streak = calculated_streak,
    updated_at = NOW()
  WHERE id = user_uuid;
  
  RETURN calculated_streak;
END;
$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql;

-- Function to update user's streak when they complete a quiz
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION update_streak_on_quiz_completion()
RETURNS TRIGGER AS $$
BEGIN
  -- Only trigger when quiz is completed
  IF NEW.quiz_completed = true AND (OLD.quiz_completed = false OR OLD.quiz_completed IS NULL) THEN
    
    -- Update user's streak
    UPDATE users 
    SET 
      streak = calculate_user_streak(NEW.user_id),
      updated_at = NOW()
    WHERE id = NEW.user_id;
  END IF;
  
  RETURN NEW;
END;
$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql;

-- Create trigger on user_progress table
DROP TRIGGER IF EXISTS trigger_update_streak_on_quiz ON user_progress;
CREATE TRIGGER trigger_update_streak_on_quiz
  AFTER UPDATE ON user_progress
  FOR EACH ROW
  EXECUTE FUNCTION update_streak_on_quiz_completion();

-- Grant permissions
GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION calculate_user_streak(UUID) TO authenticated, anon;
GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION check_and_update_streak(UUID) TO authenticated, anon;
GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION update_streak_on_quiz_completion() TO authenticated, anon;

-- Success message
SELECT 'Streak calculation function created successfully!' as status;

export const _OnesignalAppId_ = "3d9810d0-cc9e-466d-8537-df3dbe8e0acc"

  Deno.env.get('SUPABASE_URL') || '',
  Deno.env.get('SUPABASE_ANON_KEY') || ''

FILE: supabase/functions/heart-management/index.ts
================================================
import { serve } from "https://deno.land/std@0.168.0/http/server.ts"
import { createClient } from 'https://esm.sh/@supabase/supabase-js@2'

const corsHeaders = {
  'Access-Control-Allow-Origin': '*',
  'Access-Control-Allow-Headers': 'authorization, x-client-info, apikey, content-type',
}

serve(async (req) => {
  // Handle CORS preflight requests
  if (req.method === 'OPTIONS') {
    return new Response('ok', { headers: corsHeaders })
  }

  try {
    // Create Supabase client
    const supabaseUrl = Deno.env.get('SUPABASE_URL')!
    const supabaseServiceKey = Deno.env.get('SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY')!
    const supabase = createClient(supabaseUrl, supabaseServiceKey)

    const { action, userId, reason, lessonId } = await req.json()

    switch (action) {
      case 'deduct_heart':
        return await handleDeductHeart(supabase, userId, reason, lessonId)
      
      case 'replenish_hearts':
        return await handleReplenishHearts(supabase, userId)
      
      case 'get_heart_status':
        return await handleGetHeartStatus(supabase, userId)
      
      case 'check_all_replenishment':
        return await handleCheckAllReplenishment(supabase)
      
      default:
        return new Response(
          JSON.stringify({ error: 'Invalid action' }),
          { 
            status: 400, 
            headers: { ...corsHeaders, 'Content-Type': 'application/json' } 
          }
        )
    }

  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error:', error)
    return new Response(
      JSON.stringify({ error: error.message }),
      { 
        status: 500, 
        headers: { ...corsHeaders, 'Content-Type': 'application/json' } 
      }
    )
  }
})

// Deduct heart when user gets wrong answer
async function handleDeductHeart(supabase: any, userId: string, reason: string, lessonId?: string) {
  // Get current user hearts
  const { data: user, error: userError } = await supabase
    .from('users')
    .select('hearts, max_hearts')
    .eq('id', userId)
    .single()

  if (userError || !user) {
    throw new Error('User not found')
  }

  if (user.hearts <= 0) {
    throw new Error('No hearts remaining')
  }

  const previousHearts = user.hearts
  const newHearts = Math.max(0, user.hearts - 1)
  const now = new Date().toISOString()

  // Update user hearts
  const { error: updateError } = await supabase
    .from('users')
    .update({ 
      hearts: newHearts,
      last_heart_loss: now
    })
    .eq('id', userId)

  if (updateError) {
    throw new Error('Failed to update hearts')
  }

  // Record heart history
  const { error: historyError } = await supabase
    .from('heart_history')
    .insert({
      user_id: userId,
      hearts_change: -1,
      reason: reason,
      previous_hearts: previousHearts,
      new_hearts: newHearts,
      timestamp: now
    })

  if (historyError) {
    console.error('Failed to record heart history:', historyError)
  }

  return new Response(
    JSON.stringify({
      success: true,
      previousHearts,
      newHearts,
      timestamp: now
    }),
    { 
      headers: { ...corsHeaders, 'Content-Type': 'application/json' } 
    }
  )
}

// Replenish hearts after 12 hours
async function handleReplenishHearts(supabase: any, userId: string) {
  const { data: user, error: userError } = await supabase
    .from('users')
    .select('hearts, max_hearts, last_heart_loss')
    .eq('id', userId)
    .single()

  if (userError || !user) {
    throw new Error('User not found')
  }

  if (!user.last_heart_loss || user.hearts >= user.max_hearts) {
    return new Response(
      JSON.stringify({ 
        replenished: false, 
        reason: 'No replenishment needed' 
      }),
      { 
        headers: { ...corsHeaders, 'Content-Type': 'application/json' } 
      }
    )
  }

  const now = new Date()
  const lastHeartLoss = new Date(user.last_heart_loss)
  const timeSinceLoss = now.getTime() - lastHeartLoss.getTime()
  const hoursSinceLoss = timeSinceLoss / (1000 * 60 * 60)

  if (hoursSinceLoss < 5) {  // 5 hours instead of 1 minute
    return new Response(
      JSON.stringify({ 
        replenished: false, 
        reason: 'Not enough time has passed',
        timeRemaining: 5 - hoursSinceLoss
      }),
      { 
        headers: { ...corsHeaders, 'Content-Type': 'application/json' } 
      }
    )
  }

  const previousHearts = user.hearts
  const newHearts = Math.min(user.max_hearts, user.hearts + 1)
  const nowISO = now.toISOString()

  // Update user hearts
  const { error: updateError } = await supabase
    .from('users')
    .update({ 
      hearts: newHearts,
      last_heart_replenish: nowISO
    })
    .eq('id', userId)

  if (updateError) {
    throw new Error('Failed to update hearts')
  }

  // Record heart history
  const { error: historyError } = await supabase
    .from('heart_history')
    .insert({
      user_id: userId,
      hearts_change: 1,
      reason: 'replenish',
      previous_hearts: previousHearts,
      new_hearts: newHearts,
      timestamp: nowISO
    })

  if (historyError) {
    console.error('Failed to record heart history:', historyError)
  }

  return new Response(
    JSON.stringify({
      replenished: true,
      previousHearts,
      newHearts,
      timestamp: nowISO
    }),
    { 
      headers: { ...corsHeaders, 'Content-Type': 'application/json' } 
    }
  )
}

// Get current heart status
async function handleGetHeartStatus(supabase: any, userId: string) {
  const { data: user, error: userError } = await supabase
    .from('users')
    .select('hearts, max_hearts, last_heart_loss, last_heart_replenish')
    .eq('id', userId)
    .single()

  if (userError || !user) {
    throw new Error('User not found')
  }

  const now = new Date()
  const lastHeartLoss = user.last_heart_loss ? new Date(user.last_heart_loss) : null
  
  let shouldReplenish = false
  let timeUntilReplenish = 0

  if (lastHeartLoss && user.hearts < user.max_hearts) {
    const timeSinceLoss = now.getTime() - lastHeartLoss.getTime()
    const hoursSinceLoss = timeSinceLoss / (1000 * 60 * 60)
    
    if (hoursSinceLoss >= 5) {  // 5 hours instead of 1 minute
      shouldReplenish = true
    } else {
      timeUntilReplenish = 5 - hoursSinceLoss
    }
  }

  return new Response(
    JSON.stringify({
      currentHearts: user.hearts,
      maxHearts: user.max_hearts,
      shouldReplenish,
      timeUntilReplenish,
      lastHeartLoss: user.last_heart_loss,
      lastHeartReplenish: user.last_heart_replenish,
      serverTime: now.toISOString()
    }),
    { 
      headers: { ...corsHeaders, 'Content-Type': 'application/json' } 
    }
  )
}

// Check and replenish all users (for cron job)
async function handleCheckAllReplenishment(supabase: any) {
  const { data: users, error: usersError } = await supabase
    .from('users')
    .select('id, hearts, max_hearts, last_heart_loss')
    .lt('hearts', 'max_hearts')
    .not('last_heart_loss', 'is', null)

  if (usersError) {
    throw new Error('Failed to fetch users')
  }

  const now = new Date()
  let replenishedCount = 0

  for (const user of users) {
    const lastHeartLoss = new Date(user.last_heart_loss)
    const timeSinceLoss = now.getTime() - lastHeartLoss.getTime()
    const hoursSinceLoss = timeSinceLoss / (1000 * 60 * 60)

    if (hoursSinceLoss >= 5) {  // 5 hours instead of 1 minute
      const previousHearts = user.hearts
      const newHearts = Math.min(user.max_hearts, user.hearts + 1)
      const nowISO = now.toISOString()

      // Update user hearts
      const { error: updateError } = await supabase
        .from('users')
        .update({ 
          hearts: newHearts,
          last_heart_replenish: nowISO
        })
        .eq('id', user.id)

      if (!updateError) {
        // Record heart history
        await supabase
          .from('heart_history')
          .insert({
            user_id: user.id,
            hearts_change: 1,
            reason: 'replenish',
            previous_hearts: previousHearts,
            new_hearts: newHearts,
            timestamp: nowISO
          })

        replenishedCount++
      }
    }
  }

  return new Response(
    JSON.stringify({
      replenishedCount,
      totalUsers: users.length
    }),
    { 
      headers: { ...corsHeaders, 'Content-Type': 'application/json' } 
    }
  )
}

-- Function to send notification via Edge Function
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION send_notification(
  notification_type TEXT,
  notification_title TEXT,
  notification_message TEXT,
  target_user_id UUID DEFAULT NULL,
  additional_data JSONB DEFAULT '{}'::jsonb
)
RETURNS VOID
LANGUAGE plpgsql
SECURITY DEFINER
AS $$
DECLARE
  edge_function_url TEXT;
  response_status INTEGER;
  response_body TEXT;
BEGIN
  -- Get the Edge Function URL from environment
  edge_function_url := 'https://' || current_setting('request.header.host') || '/functions/v1/send-notification';
  
  -- Make HTTP request to Edge Function
  SELECT 
    status,
    content
  INTO 
    response_status,
    response_body
  FROM 
    net.http_post(
      url := edge_function_url,
      headers := '{"Content-Type": "application/json", "Authorization": "Bearer ' || current_setting('request.header.apikey') || '"}',
      body := json_build_object(
        'type', notification_type,
        'title', notification_title,
        'message', notification_message,
        'userId', target_user_id,
        'data', additional_data
      )::text
    );
  
  -- Log the response
  RAISE NOTICE 'Notification sent: % - Status: % - Response: %', 
    notification_type, response_status, response_body;
    
  -- Check if request was successful
  IF response_status != 200 THEN
    RAISE WARNING 'Failed to send notification: % - Status: %', notification_type, response_status;
  END IF;
  
EXCEPTION
  WHEN OTHERS THEN
    RAISE WARNING 'Error sending notification: % - Error: %', notification_type, SQLERRM;
END;
$$;

-- Function to send daily challenge notification

AS $$
BEGIN

    'daily_challenge',

    'New financial literacy questions are waiting for you. Keep your streak alive!',
    NULL, -- Send to all users
    '{"action": "navigate_to_daily_challenge"}'
  );
END;
$$;

$$;

-- Function to send quiz reminder notification
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION send_quiz_reminder_notification(
  user_id UUID
)
RETURNS VOID
LANGUAGE plpgsql
SECURITY DEFINER
AS $$
BEGIN
  PERFORM send_notification(
    'quiz_reminder',
    'Ã°Å¸â€œÅ¡ Time for a Quiz!',
    'Keep your streak alive! Take a quick quiz now.',
    user_id,
    json_build_object(
      'action', 'navigate_to_lessons'
    )
  );
END;
$$;

-- Grant execute permissions to authenticated users
GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION send_notification(TEXT, TEXT, TEXT, UUID, JSONB) TO authenticated;
GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION send_daily_challenge_notification() TO authenticated;
GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION send_friend_request_notification(UUID, TEXT, UUID) TO authenticated;
GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION send_streak_warning_notification(UUID, INTEGER) TO authenticated;
GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION send_level_up_notification(UUID, TEXT, INTEGER) TO authenticated;
GRANT EXECUTE ON FUNCTION send_quiz_reminder_notification(UUID) TO authenticated;

-- ========================================
-- DATABASE TRIGGERS
-- ========================================

-- Trigger for friend requests
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION trigger_friend_request_notification()
RETURNS TRIGGER
LANGUAGE plpgsql
AS $$
BEGIN
  -- Only send notification when a new friend request is created
  IF NEW.status = 'pending' AND TG_OP = 'INSERT' THEN
    -- Get requester name
    DECLARE
      requester_name TEXT;
    BEGIN
      SELECT name INTO requester_name FROM users WHERE id = NEW.user_id;
      
      -- Send notification to the friend being requested
      PERFORM send_friend_request_notification(
        NEW.user_id,
        COALESCE(requester_name, 'Someone'),
        NEW.friend_id
      );
    END;
  END IF;
  
  RETURN NEW;
END;
$$;

-- Create the trigger
DROP TRIGGER IF EXISTS friend_request_notification_trigger ON friends;
CREATE TRIGGER friend_request_notification_trigger
  AFTER INSERT ON friends
  FOR EACH ROW
  EXECUTE FUNCTION trigger_friend_request_notification();

-- Trigger for level up notifications
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION trigger_level_up_notification()
RETURNS TRIGGER
LANGUAGE plpgsql
AS $$
BEGIN
  -- Check if rank changed (level up)
  IF OLD.rank IS NOT NULL AND NEW.rank != OLD.rank THEN
    -- Calculate XP gained (you might want to adjust this logic)
    DECLARE
      xp_gained INTEGER;
    BEGIN
      xp_gained := NEW.xp - OLD.xp;
      
      -- Send level up notification
      PERFORM send_level_up_notification(
        NEW.id,
        NEW.rank,
        xp_gained
      );
    END;
  END IF;
  
  RETURN NEW;
END;
$$;

-- Create the trigger
DROP TRIGGER IF EXISTS level_up_notification_trigger ON users;
CREATE TRIGGER level_up_notification_trigger
  AFTER UPDATE ON users
  FOR EACH ROW
  EXECUTE FUNCTION trigger_level_up_notification();

-- Trigger for streak warnings (when streak is about to break)
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION trigger_streak_warning_notification()
RETURNS TRIGGER
LANGUAGE plpgsql
AS $$
BEGIN
  -- Check if streak is at risk (streak > 0 but last activity was more than 24 hours ago)
  IF NEW.streak > 0 THEN
    -- You might want to add additional logic here to check last activity time
    -- For now, we'll just log that the function exists
    RAISE NOTICE 'Streak warning check for user % with streak %', NEW.id, NEW.streak;
  END IF;
  
  RETURN NEW;
END;
$$;

-- Create the trigger
DROP TRIGGER IF EXISTS streak_warning_notification_trigger ON users;
CREATE TRIGGER streak_warning_notification_trigger
  AFTER UPDATE ON users
  FOR EACH ROW
  EXECUTE FUNCTION trigger_streak_warning_notification();

export const fonts = {
  // Parkinsans Font Family
  regular: 'Parkinsans-Regular',
  light: 'Parkinsans-Light',
  medium: 'Parkinsans-Medium',
  semiBold: 'Parkinsans-SemiBold',
  bold: 'Parkinsans-Bold',
  extraBold: 'Parkinsans-ExtraBold',
} as const;

export type FontWeight = keyof typeof fonts;

// Font weight mapping for easy use
export const fontWeights = {
  light: fonts.light,
  normal: fonts.regular,
  medium: fonts.medium,
  semiBold: fonts.semiBold,
  bold: fonts.bold,
  extraBold: fonts.extraBold,
} as const;

FILE: utils/heartUtils.ts
================================================
import { supabase } from '../services/supabase';

// Deduct heart when user gets wrong answer
export const deductHeart = async (userId: string, reason: string, lessonId?: string) => {
  try {
    // Get current user hearts
    const { data: user, error: userError } = await supabase
      .from('users')
      .select('hearts, max_hearts')
      .eq('id', userId)
      .single();

    if (userError || !user) {
      throw new Error('User not found');
    }

    if (user.hearts <= 0) {
      throw new Error('No hearts remaining');
    }

    const previousHearts = user.hearts;
    const newHearts = Math.max(0, user.hearts - 1);
    const now = new Date().toISOString();

    // Update user hearts
    const { error: updateError } = await supabase
      .from('users')
      .update({ 
        hearts: newHearts,
        last_heart_loss: now
      })
      .eq('id', userId);

    if (updateError) {
      throw new Error('Failed to update hearts');
    }

    // Record heart history
    const { error: historyError } = await supabase
      .from('heart_history')
      .insert({
        user_id: userId,
        hearts_change: -1,
        reason: reason,
        previous_hearts: previousHearts,
        new_hearts: newHearts,
        timestamp: now
      });

    if (historyError) {
      console.error('Failed to record heart history:', historyError);
    }

    return {
      success: true,
      previousHearts,
      newHearts,
      timestamp: now
    };
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error deducting heart:', error);
    throw error;
  }
};

// Get heart status for a user
export const getHeartStatus = async (userId: string) => {
  try {
    const { data: user, error: userError } = await supabase
      .from('users')
      .select('hearts, max_hearts, last_heart_loss, last_heart_replenish')
      .eq('id', userId)
      .single();

    if (userError || !user) {
      throw new Error('User not found');
    }

    const now = new Date();
    const lastHeartLoss = user.last_heart_loss ? new Date(user.last_heart_loss) : null;
    
    let shouldReplenish = false;
    let timeUntilReplenish = 0;

    if (lastHeartLoss && user.hearts < user.max_hearts) {
      const timeSinceLoss = now.getTime() - lastHeartLoss.getTime();
      const hoursSinceLoss = timeSinceLoss / (1000 * 60 * 60);
      
      if (hoursSinceLoss >= 5) {
        shouldReplenish = true;
      } else {
        timeUntilReplenish = 5 - hoursSinceLoss;
      }
    }

    return {
      currentHearts: user.hearts || 5,
      maxHearts: user.max_hearts || 5,
      shouldReplenish,
      timeUntilReplenish,
      lastHeartLoss: user.last_heart_loss,
      lastHeartReplenish: user.last_heart_replenish,
      serverTime: now.toISOString()
    };
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error getting heart status:', error);
    throw error;
  }
};

// Initialize hearts for a new user
export const initializeUserHearts = async (userId: string) => {
  try {
    const now = new Date().toISOString();
    
    const { error: updateError } = await supabase
      .from('users')
      .update({
        hearts: 5,
        max_hearts: 5,
        last_heart_replenish: now
      })
      .eq('id', userId);

    if (updateError) {
      throw new Error('Failed to initialize hearts');
    }

    return { 
      initialized: true, 
      hearts: 5,
      maxHearts: 5 
    };
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error initializing user hearts:', error);
    throw error;
  }
};

// Check if user has enough hearts to continue learning
export const canUserLearn = async (userId: string): Promise<boolean> => {
  try {
    const { data: user, error: userError } = await supabase
      .from('users')
      .select('hearts')
      .eq('id', userId)
      .single();

    if (userError || !user) {
      return false;
    }

    return user.hearts > 0;
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error checking if user can learn:', error);
    return false;
  }
};

FILE: utils/responsive.ts
================================================
import { Dimensions, PixelRatio, Platform } from 'react-native';
import { fonts } from './fonts';

const { width: SCREEN_WIDTH, height: SCREEN_HEIGHT } = Dimensions.get('window');

// Base dimensions (using Pixel 7a as reference)
const baseWidth = 393; // Pixel 7a width
const baseHeight = 851; // Pixel 7a height

// Scale factors
const widthScale = SCREEN_WIDTH / baseWidth;
const heightScale = SCREEN_HEIGHT / baseHeight;

// Responsive sizing functions
export const wp = (percentage: number) => {
  return (SCREEN_WIDTH * percentage) / 100;
};

export const hp = (percentage: number) => {
  return (SCREEN_HEIGHT * percentage) / 100;
};

export const normalize = (size: number) => {
  const newSize = size * widthScale;
  if (Platform.OS === 'ios') {
    return Math.round(PixelRatio.roundToNearestPixel(newSize));
  } else {
    return Math.round(PixelRatio.roundToNearestPixel(newSize)) - 2;
  }
};

export const normalizeFont = (size: number) => {
  const newSize = size * widthScale;
  if (Platform.OS === 'ios') {
    return Math.round(PixelRatio.roundToNearestPixel(newSize));
  } else {
    return Math.round(PixelRatio.roundToNearestPixel(newSize)) - 1;
  }
};

// Responsive spacing
export const spacing = {
  xs: normalize(4),
  sm: normalize(8),
  md: normalize(12),
  lg: normalize(16),
  xl: normalize(20),
  xxl: normalize(24),
  xxxl: normalize(32),
};

// Responsive font sizes
export const fontSize = {
  xs: normalizeFont(10),
  sm: normalizeFont(12),
  md: normalizeFont(14),
  lg: normalizeFont(16),
  xl: normalizeFont(18),
  xxl: normalizeFont(20),
  xxxl: normalizeFont(24),
  title: normalizeFont(28),
};

// Responsive icon sizes
export const iconSize = {
  xs: normalize(12),
  sm: normalize(16),
  md: normalize(20),
  lg: normalize(24),
  xl: normalize(32),
  xxl: normalize(48),
  xxxl: normalize(80),
};

// Screen dimensions
export const screenDimensions = {
  width: SCREEN_WIDTH,
  height: SCREEN_HEIGHT,
  scale: widthScale,
};

// Responsive card dimensions
export const cardDimensions = {
  small: {
    width: wp(45),
    height: hp(8),
  },
  medium: {
    width: wp(90),
    height: hp(12),
  },
  large: {
    width: wp(90),
    height: hp(15),
  },
};

// Responsive button dimensions
export const buttonDimensions = {
  small: {
    width: wp(25),
    height: hp(5),
  },
  medium: {
    width: wp(40),
    height: hp(6),
  },
  large: {
    width: wp(70),
    height: hp(7),
  },
};

// Font utilities
export const fontFamily = fonts;

// Helper function to get font style object
export const getFontStyle = (weight: keyof typeof fonts = 'regular', size?: number) => ({
  fontFamily: fonts[weight],
  fontSize: size ? normalizeFont(size) : undefined,
});

// Common font styles
export const fontStyles = {
  light: (size?: number) => getFontStyle('light', size),
  regular: (size?: number) => getFontStyle('regular', size),
  medium: (size?: number) => getFontStyle('medium', size),
  semiBold: (size?: number) => getFontStyle('semiBold', size),
  bold: (size?: number) => getFontStyle('bold', size),
  extraBold: (size?: number) => getFontStyle('extraBold', size),
};
